frcInboundChangeOrdersDampened.name: frcInboundChangeOrdersDampened
frcInboundChangeOrdersDampened.description: The number of change orders received from the partner associated with this connection that have been filtered out by the inbound dampening check.

frcJoinNotificationsReceived.name: frcJoinNotificationsReceived
frcJoinNotificationsReceived.description: The number of partner join notifications received from the partner associated with this connection.

frcJoinNotificationsSent.name: frcJoinNotificationsSent
frcJoinNotificationsSent.description: The number of partner join requests (if this is an inbound connection) or ready-to-join notifications (if this is an outbound connection) sent to the partner associated with this connection.

frcJoins.name: frcJoins
frcJoins.description: The number of successful joins with the partner associated with this connection.

frcLocalChangeOrdersSent.name: frcLocalChangeOrdersSent
frcLocalChangeOrdersSent.description: The number of locally originated replication change orders that have been sent to the partner associated with this connection.

frcLocalChangeOrdersSentAtJoin.name: frcLocalChangeOrdersSentAtJoin
frcLocalChangeOrdersSentAtJoin.description: The number of locally originated replication change orders produced by a partner induced version vector scan that have been sent to the partner associated with this connection.

frcOutboundChangeOrdersDampened.name: frcOutboundChangeOrdersDampened
frcOutboundChangeOrdersDampened.description: The number of change orders sent to the partner associated with this connection that have been filtered out by the outbound dampening check and thus were never sent.

frcPacketsSent.name: frcPacketsSent
frcPacketsSent.description: The total number of FRS data and control packets sent to the partner associated with this connection.

frcPacketsSentInBytes.name: frcPacketsSentInBytes
frcPacketsSentInBytes.description: The total number of FRS data and control bytes sent to the partner associated with this connection.

frcPacketsSentInError.name: frcPacketsSentInError
frcPacketsSentInError.description: The cumulative number of FRS data or control packets not sent because of some error condition associated with this connection.

frcRemoteChangeOrdersReceived.name: frcRemoteChangeOrdersReceived
frcRemoteChangeOrdersReceived.description: The number of change orders received from the partner associated with this connection that have passed the inbound dampening check.

frcRemoteChangeOrdersSent.name: frcRemoteChangeOrdersSent
frcRemoteChangeOrdersSent.description: The number of replication change orders originating upstream from this member (i.e. remote) that have been sent to the partner associated with this connection.

frcUnjoins.name: frcUnjoins
frcUnjoins.description: The number of unjoins with the partner associated with this connection.

fileReplicaSetTable.name: fileReplicaSetTable
fileReplicaSetTable.description: The FileReplicaSet performance object displays performance statistics of the REPLICASET object that defines a replica set (one or more replicas, shared volumes or directories that store duplicates of the contents of an original share). The object reports statistics for the computer that constitutes the original share. For example, in a bidirectional ring topology of three computers A, B, and C, where computer A and computer C both replicate from computer B, the FileReplicaSet counters would provide data for computer B.

fileReplicaSetEntry.name: fileReplicaSetEntry
fileReplicaSetEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'FileReplicaSet' object.

frsAuthentications.name: frsAuthentications
frsAuthentications.description: The number of successful authentication checks made on packets received from any partner associated with this replica set member.

frsAuthenticationsInError.name: frsAuthenticationsInError
frsAuthenticationsInError.description: The cumulative number of authentication check failures detected on packets received from any partner associated with this replica set member.

frsBindings.name: frsBindings
frsBindings.description: The number of successful RPC bind requests to the FRS server on any partner associated with this replica set member.

frsBindingsInError.name: frsBindingsInError
frsBindingsInError.description: The cumulative number of unsuccessful RPC bind requests to the FRS server on any partner associated with this replica set member.

frsBytesOfFilesInstalled.name: frsBytesOfFilesInstalled
frsBytesOfFilesInstalled.description: The total number of bytes of staging file data that have been installed on this replica set member.

frsBytesOfStagingFetched.name: frsBytesOfStagingFetched
frsBytesOfStagingFetched.description: The total number of bytes of staging file data received by this replica set member from its inbound partners.

frsBytesOfStagingGenerated.name: frsBytesOfStagingGenerated
frsBytesOfStagingGenerated.description: The total number of bytes of staging file data generated by this replica set member not including the number of bytes produced as part of regeneration.

frsBytesOfStagingRegenerated.name: frsBytesOfStagingRegenerated
frsBytesOfStagingRegenerated.description: The total number of bytes of staging file data regenerated by this replica set member for a specific outbound partner request.

frsChgOrdersAborted.name: frsChgOrdersAborted
frsChgOrdersAborted.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that were aborted on this replica set member.

frsChgOrdersEvaporated.name: frsChgOrdersEvaporated
frsChgOrdersEvaporated.description: The number of local file updates that were never processed because the underlying file was deleted first.

frsChgOrdersIssued.name: frsChgOrdersIssued
frsChgOrdersIssued.description: The number of local plus remote file updates initiated on this replica set member.

frsChgOrdersMorphed.name: frsChgOrdersMorphed
frsChgOrdersMorphed.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that encountered a name space collision on this replica set member.

frsChgOrdersPropagated.name: frsChgOrdersPropagated
frsChgOrdersPropagated.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that were propagated to the outbound log of this replica set member. The update remains pending in the outbound log until it has been delivered to all outbound partners.

frsChgOrdersReceived.name: frsChgOrdersReceived
frsChgOrdersReceived.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that have been received by this replica set member. Note that depending on the replication topology it is possible for the same remote file update to be sent from multiple inbound partners. However, only one will send the actual file data.

frsChgOrdersRetired.name: frsChgOrdersRetired
frsChgOrdersRetired.description: The number of local plus remote file updates retired on this replica set member.

frsChgOrdersRetried.name: frsChgOrdersRetried
frsChgOrdersRetried.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that were retried for any reason on this replica set member.

frsChgOrdersRetriedFetch.name: frsChgOrdersRetriedFetch
frsChgOrdersRetriedFetch.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that were retried due to a stage file fetch problem on this replica set member.

frsChgOrdersRetriedGenerate.name: frsChgOrdersRetriedGenerate
frsChgOrdersRetriedGenerate.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that were retried due to a stage file generation problem on this replica set member.

frsChgOrdersRetriedInstall.name: frsChgOrdersRetriedInstall
frsChgOrdersRetriedInstall.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that were retried due to a stage file install problem on this replica set member. Most likely caused by a sharing conflict trying to access the target file or directory.

frsChgOrdersRetriedRename.name: frsChgOrdersRetriedRename
frsChgOrdersRetriedRename.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that were retried due to a problem during the final target file rename or delete operation on this replica set member. Most likely caused by a sharing conflict trying to access the target file or directory.

frsChgOrdersSent.name: frsChgOrdersSent
frsChgOrdersSent.description: The number of local plus remote file updates that have been sent to the outbound partners of this replica set member.

frsCommunicationTimeouts.name: frsCommunicationTimeouts
frsCommunicationTimeouts.description: The cumulative number of FRS data or control packets not sent to an outbound partner because the send request timed out.

frsDSBindings.name: frsDSBindings
frsDSBindings.description: The number of times FRS has attempted to acquire a binding handle to the active directory.

frsDSBindingsInError.name: frsDSBindingsInError
frsDSBindingsInError.description: The cumulative number of attempts to acquire a binding handle to the active directory that failed with some error status.

frsDSObjects.name: frsDSObjects
frsDSObjects.description: The number of FRS configuration Objects retreived from the directory service.

frsDSObjectsInError.name: frsDSObjectsInError
frsDSObjectsInError.description: The cumulative count of FRS configuration objects retreived from the directory service that were missing either the distinguished name, object GUID or the relative distinguished name attributes.

frsDSPolls.name: frsDSPolls
frsDSPolls.description: The number of times FRS has polled the active directory for FRS configuration information on this computer.

frsDSPollsWithChgs.name: frsDSPollsWithChgs
frsDSPollsWithChgs.description: The number of times FRS has polled the active directory for FRS configuration information and configuration changes were found.

frsDSPollsWithoutChgs.name: frsDSPollsWithoutChgs
frsDSPollsWithoutChgs.description: The number of times FRS has polled the active directory for FRS configuration information and no configuration changes were found.

frsDSSearches.name: frsDSSearches
frsDSSearches.description: The number of times FRS has made a search request to the active directory.

frsDSSearchesInError.name: frsDSSearchesInError
frsDSSearchesInError.description: The cumulative number of times FRS has made a search request to the active directory and the request returned with an error condition.

frsFetchBlocksReceived.name: frsFetchBlocksReceived
frsFetchBlocksReceived.description: The number of blocks of staging file data received from all inbound partners associated with this replica set member. The underlying transport may break a block into a smaller number of packets on the wire.

frsFetchBlocksReceivedInBytes.name: frsFetchBlocksReceivedInBytes
frsFetchBlocksReceivedInBytes.description: The total number of bytes of staging file data received by this replica set member from all inbound partners.

frsFetchBlocksSent.name: frsFetchBlocksSent
frsFetchBlocksSent.description: The number of blocks of staging file data sent to any outbound partner associated with this replica set member. The underlying transport may break a block into a smaller number of packets on the wire.

frsFetchBlocksSentInBytes.name: frsFetchBlocksSentInBytes
frsFetchBlocksSentInBytes.description: The total number of bytes of staging file data sent to the outbound partners of this replica set member.

frsFetchRequestsReceived.name: frsFetchRequestsReceived
frsFetchRequestsReceived.description: The number of staging files received from all inbound partners associated with this replica set member.

frsFetchRequestsSent.name: frsFetchRequestsSent
frsFetchRequestsSent.description: The number of staging files requested from any inbound partner associated with this replica set member.

frsFilesInstalled.name: frsFilesInstalled
frsFilesInstalled.description: The number of file updates and deletes performed on this replica set member.

frsFilesInstalledWithError.name: frsFilesInstalledWithError
frsFilesInstalledWithError.description: The cumulative number of file updates that were aborted because of some non-recoverable error.

frsInboundChgOrdersDampened.name: frsInboundChgOrdersDampened
frsInboundChgOrdersDampened.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that were dampened because the update was already delivered by another member.

frsJoinNotificationsReceived.name: frsJoinNotificationsReceived
frsJoinNotificationsReceived.description: The number of partner join notifications received from all inbound partners associated with this replica set member.

frsJoinNotificationsSent.name: frsJoinNotificationsSent
frsJoinNotificationsSent.description: The number of inbound partner join requests or outbound partner ready-to-join notifications sent to all partners associated with this replica set member.

frsJoins.name: frsJoins
frsJoins.description: The number of successful joins with any partner associated with this replica set member.

frsKBOfStagingSpaceFree.name: frsKBOfStagingSpaceFree
frsKBOfStagingSpaceFree.description: The amount of staging space (in Kilobyte units) currently available within the staging space limit. Note that there may not actually be this amount of free space left on the staging volume.

frsKBOfStagingSpaceInUse.name: frsKBOfStagingSpaceInUse
frsKBOfStagingSpaceInUse.description: The amount of staging space (in Kilobyte units) currently in use.

frsLocalChgOrdersAborted.name: frsLocalChgOrdersAborted
frsLocalChgOrdersAborted.description: The number of locally originated file updates that were aborted. Most likely because a file was deleted before a change to it could be propagated so no stage file could be generated.

frsLocalChgOrdersIssued.name: frsLocalChgOrdersIssued
frsLocalChgOrdersIssued.description: The number of locally originated file updates initiated on this replica set member.

frsLocalChgOrdersMorphed.name: frsLocalChgOrdersMorphed
frsLocalChgOrdersMorphed.description: The number of locally originated file updates that encountered a name space collision on this replica set member. Most likely caused by the reanimation of a parent dir.

frsLocalChgOrdersPropagated.name: frsLocalChgOrdersPropagated
frsLocalChgOrdersPropagated.description: The number of locally originated file updates that were propagated to the outbound log of this replica set member. The update remains pending in the outbound log until it has been delivered to all outbound partners.

frsLocalChgOrdersRetired.name: frsLocalChgOrdersRetired
frsLocalChgOrdersRetired.description: The number of locally originated file updates retired on this replica set member.

frsLocalChgOrdersRetried.name: frsLocalChgOrdersRetried
frsLocalChgOrdersRetried.description: The number of locally originated file updates that were retried for any reason on this replica set member.

frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedFetch.name: frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedFetch
frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedFetch.description: The number of locally originated file updates that were retried due to a stage file fetch problem on this replica set member.

frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedGenerate.name: frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedGenerate
frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedGenerate.description: The number of locally originated file updates that were retried due to a stage file generation problem on this replica set member. Most likely caused by a sharing conflict trying to access the target file.

frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedInstall.name: frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedInstall
frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedInstall.description: The number of locally originated file updates that were retried due to a stage file install problem on this replica set member. Most likely caused by a sharing conflict trying to access the target file or directory.

frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedRename.name: frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedRename
frsLocalChgOrdersRetriedRename.description: The number of locally originated file updates that were retried due to a problem during the final target file rename or delete operation on this replica set member. Most likely caused by a sharing conflict trying to access the target file or directory.

frsLocalChgOrdersSent.name: frsLocalChgOrdersSent
frsLocalChgOrdersSent.description: The number of locally originated file updates that have been sent to the outbound partners of this replica set member.

frsLocalChgOrdersSentJoin.name: frsLocalChgOrdersSentJoin
frsLocalChgOrdersSentJoin.description: The number of locally originated file updates which were created by a partner induced version vector scan that have been sent to the outbound partners of this replica set member.

frsOutboundChgOrdersDampened.name: frsOutboundChgOrdersDampened
frsOutboundChgOrdersDampened.description: The number of pending outbound file updates that were dampened because the outbound partner has already received it from another source.

frsPacketsReceived.name: frsPacketsReceived
frsPacketsReceived.description: The number of FRS data or control packets (RPC calls) received by FRS.

frsPacketsReceivedInBytes.name: frsPacketsReceivedInBytes
frsPacketsReceivedInBytes.description: The total number of FRS data and control bytes received by all replica sets on this computer.

frsPacketsReceivedInError.name: frsPacketsReceivedInError
frsPacketsReceivedInError.description: The cumulative number of FRS data or control packets received that were out of rev or otherwise malformed.

frsPacketsSent.name: frsPacketsSent
frsPacketsSent.description: The number of FRS data and control packets sent to all outbound partners associated with this replica set member.

frsPacketsSentInBytes.name: frsPacketsSentInBytes
frsPacketsSentInBytes.description: The total number of FRS data and control bytes sent by this replica set member to other members.

frsPacketsSentInError.name: frsPacketsSentInError
frsPacketsSentInError.description: The cumulative number of FRS data or control packets not sent to an outbound partner because of some error condition.

frsRemoteChgOrdersAborted.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersAborted
frsRemoteChgOrdersAborted.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that were aborted. Most likely because of an attempt to fetch a staging file from an inbound partner and the partner no longer has the file because it has been deleted.

frsRemoteChgOrdersIssued.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersIssued
frsRemoteChgOrdersIssued.description: The number of remotely originated file updates initiated on this replica set member.

frsRemoteChgOrdersMorphed.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersMorphed
frsRemoteChgOrdersMorphed.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that encountered a name space collision on this replica set member. Most likely caused by simultaneous create of a file or directory with the same name on more than one replica set member.

frsRemoteChgOrdersPropagated.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersPropagated
frsRemoteChgOrdersPropagated.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that were propagated to the outbound log of this replica set member. The update remains pending in the outbound log until it has been delivered to all outbound partners.

frsRemoteChgOrdersReceived.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersReceived
frsRemoteChgOrdersReceived.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that have been received by this replica set member. Note that depending on the replication topology it is possible for the same file update to be sent from multiple inbound partners. However, only one will send the actual file data.

frsRemoteChgOrdersRetired.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersRetired
frsRemoteChgOrdersRetired.description: The number of remotely originated file updates retired on this replica set member.

frsRemoteChgOrdersRetried.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersRetried
frsRemoteChgOrdersRetried.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that were retried for any reason on this replica set member.

frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedFetch.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedFetch
frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedFetch.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that were retried due to a stage file fetch problem on this replica set member.

frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedGenerat.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedGenerat
frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedGenerat.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that were retried due to a stage file generation problem on this replica set member.

frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedInstall.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedInstall
frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedInstall.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that were retried due to a stage file install problem on this replica set member. Most likely caused by a sharing conflict trying to access the target file or directory.

frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedRename.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedRename
frsRemoteChgOrdersRetriedRename.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that were retried due to a problem during the final target file rename or delete operation on this replica set member. Most likely caused by a sharing conflict trying to access the target file or directory.

frsRemoteChgOrdersSent.name: frsRemoteChgOrdersSent
frsRemoteChgOrdersSent.description: The number of remotely originated file updates that have been sent to the outbound partners of this replica set member.

frsReplicaSetsCreated.name: frsReplicaSetsCreated
frsReplicaSetsCreated.description: The cumulative number of replica sets to which this computer has been added as a member.

frsReplicaSetsDeleted.name: frsReplicaSetsDeleted
frsReplicaSetsDeleted.description: The cumulative number of replica sets from which this computer's membership has been provisionally deleted, but could still be reanimated.

frsReplicaSetsRemoved.name: frsReplicaSetsRemoved
frsReplicaSetsRemoved.description: The cumulative number of replica sets from which this computer's membership has been permanently deleted.

frsReplicaSetsStarted.name: frsReplicaSetsStarted
frsReplicaSetsStarted.description: The number of replica sets for which processing has been started.

frsStagingFilesFetched.name: frsStagingFilesFetched
frsStagingFilesFetched.description: The number of staging files requested by this replica set member.

frsStagingFilesGenerated.name: frsStagingFilesGenerated
frsStagingFilesGenerated.description: The number of staging files generated by this replica set member.

frsStagingFilesGeneratedWithErr.name: frsStagingFilesGeneratedWithErr
frsStagingFilesGeneratedWithErr.description: The cumulative number of staging files generated by this replica set member where an error was detected during generation.

frsStagingFilesRegenerated.name: frsStagingFilesRegenerated
frsStagingFilesRegenerated.description: The number of staging files regenerated by this replica set member for a specific outbound partner request.

frsThreadsExited.name: frsThreadsExited
frsThreadsExited.description: The number of execution threads that have terminated.

frsThreadsStarted.name: frsThreadsStarted
frsThreadsStarted.description: The number of new execution threads started.

frsUnjoins.name: frsUnjoins
frsUnjoins.description: The number of unjoins with any partner associated with this replica set member.

frsUsnReads.name: frsUsnReads
frsUsnReads.description: The number of times FRS has initiated a read on the NTFRS change log. Each volume has its own change log.

frsUsnRecordsAccepted.name: frsUsnRecordsAccepted
frsUsnRecordsAccepted.description: The number of NTFS change log records accepted by FRS for further processing.

frsUsnRecordsExamined.name: frsUsnRecordsExamined
frsUsnRecordsExamined.description: The number of NTFS change log records examined by FRS.

frsUsnRecordsRejected.name: frsUsnRecordsRejected
frsUsnRecordsRejected.description: The number of NTFS change log records skipped by FRS. Most likely because the change log record was for a file not part of any active replica set.

ftpServiceTable.name: ftpServiceTable
ftpServiceTable.description: The FTP Service performance object consists of counters that show data about the Internet Information Services FTP service.

ftpServiceEntry.name: ftpServiceEntry
ftpServiceEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'FTP Service' object.

ftpSvcBytesReceivedPerSec.name: ftpSvcBytesReceivedPerSec
ftpSvcBytesReceivedPerSec.description: Bytes Received/sec is the rate that data bytes are received by the FTP service.

ftpSvcBytesSentPerSec.name: ftpSvcBytesSentPerSec
ftpSvcBytesSentPerSec.description: Bytes Sent/sec is the rate that data bytes are sent by the FTP service.

ftpSvcBytesTotalPerSec.name: ftpSvcBytesTotalPerSec
ftpSvcBytesTotalPerSec.description: Bytes Total/sec is the sum of Bytes Sent/sec and Bytes Received/sec. This is the total rate of bytes transferred by the FTP service.

ftpSvcCurrentAnonymousUsers.name: ftpSvcCurrentAnonymousUsers
ftpSvcCurrentAnonymousUsers.description: Current Anonymous Users is the number of users who currently have an anonymous connection using the FTP service.

ftpSvcCurrentConnections.name: ftpSvcCurrentConnections
ftpSvcCurrentConnections.description: Current Connections is the current number of connections established with the FTP service.

ftpSvcCurrentNonAnonymousUsers.name: ftpSvcCurrentNonAnonymousUsers
ftpSvcCurrentNonAnonymousUsers.description: Current NonAnonymous Users is the number of users who currently have a non-anonymous connection using the FTP service.

ftpSvcFTPServiceUptime.name: ftpSvcFTPServiceUptime
ftpSvcFTPServiceUptime.description: FTP Serive and FTP site uptime in seconds.

ftpSvcMaximumAnonymousUsers.name: ftpSvcMaximumAnonymousUsers
ftpSvcMaximumAnonymousUsers.description: Maximum Anonymous Users is the maximum number of users who established concurrent anonymous connections using the FTP service (since service startup).

ftpSvcMaximumConnections.name: ftpSvcMaximumConnections
ftpSvcMaximumConnections.description: Maximum Connections is the maximum number of simultaneous connections established with the FTP service.

ftpSvcMaximumNonAnonymousUsers.name: ftpSvcMaximumNonAnonymousUsers
ftpSvcMaximumNonAnonymousUsers.description: Maximum NonAnonymous Users is the maximum number of users who established concurrent non-anonymous connections using the FTP service (since service startup).

ftpSvcTotalAnonymousUsers.name: ftpSvcTotalAnonymousUsers
ftpSvcTotalAnonymousUsers.description: Total Anonymous Users is the total number of users who established an anonymous connection with the FTP service (since service startup).

ftpSvcTotalConnAttemptsAllInst.name: ftpSvcTotalConnAttemptsAllInst
ftpSvcTotalConnAttemptsAllInst.description: Total Connection Attempts is the number of connections that have been attempted using the FTP service (since service startup). This counter is for all instances listed.

ftpSvcTotalFilesReceived.name: ftpSvcTotalFilesReceived
ftpSvcTotalFilesReceived.description: Total Files Received is the total number of files received by the FTP service since service startup.

ftpSvcTotalFilesSent.name: ftpSvcTotalFilesSent
ftpSvcTotalFilesSent.description: Total Files Sent is the total number of files sent by the FTP service since service startup.

ftpSvcTotalFilesTransferred.name: ftpSvcTotalFilesTransferred
ftpSvcTotalFilesTransferred.description: Total Files Transferred is the sum of Files Sent and Files Received. This is the total number of files transferred by the FTP service since service startup.

ftpSvcTotalLogonAttempts.name: ftpSvcTotalLogonAttempts
ftpSvcTotalLogonAttempts.description: Total Logon Attempts is the number of logons that have been attempted using the FTP service (since service startup).

ftpSvcTotalNonAnonymousUsers.name: ftpSvcTotalNonAnonymousUsers
ftpSvcTotalNonAnonymousUsers.description: Total NonAnonymous Users is the total number of users who established a non-anonymous connection with the FTP service (since service startup).

gatewayServiceForNetWare.name: gatewayServiceForNetWare
gatewayServiceForNetWare.description: The Gateway for NetWare Service performance object consists of counters that measure packet transmission rates and activity of the Gateway for NetWare service.

nwBytesReceivedPerSec.name: nwBytesReceivedPerSec
nwBytesReceivedPerSec.description: Bytes Received/sec is the rate of bytes coming in to the Redirector from the network. It includes all application data as well as network protocol information (such as packet headers).

nwBytesTotalPerSec.name: nwBytesTotalPerSec
nwBytesTotalPerSec.description: Bytes Total/sec is the rate the Redirector is processing data bytes. This includes all application and file data in addition to protocol information such as packet headers.

nwBytesTransmittedPerSec.name: nwBytesTransmittedPerSec
nwBytesTransmittedPerSec.description: Bytes Transmitted/sec is the rate at which bytes are leaving the Redirector to the network. It includes all application data as well as network protocol information (such as packet headers and the like).

nwConnectNetWare2X.name: nwConnectNetWare2X
nwConnectNetWare2X.description: Connect NetWare 2.x counts connections to NetWare 2.x servers.

nwConnectNetWare3X.name: nwConnectNetWare3X
nwConnectNetWare3X.description: Connect NetWare 3.x counts connections to NetWare 3.x servers.

nwConnectNetWare4X.name: nwConnectNetWare4X
nwConnectNetWare4X.description: Connect NetWare 4.x counts connections to NetWare 4.x servers.

nwFileDataOperationsPerSec.name: nwFileDataOperationsPerSec
nwFileDataOperationsPerSec.description: File Data Operations/sec is the rate the Redirector is processing data operations. One operation includes (hopefully) many bytes. We say hopefully here because each operation has overhead. You can determine the efficiency of this path by dividing the Bytes/sec by this counter to determine the average number of bytes transferred/operation.

nwFileReadOperationsPerSec.name: nwFileReadOperationsPerSec
nwFileReadOperationsPerSec.description: File Read Operations/sec is the rate at which applications are asking the Redirector for data. Each call to a file system or similar Application Program Interface (API) call counts as one operation.

nwFileWriteOperationsPerSec.name: nwFileWriteOperationsPerSec
nwFileWriteOperationsPerSec.description: File Write Operations/sec is the rate at which applications are sending data to the Redirector. Each call to a file system or similar Application Program Interface (API) call counts as one operation.

nwPacketBurstIOPerSec.name: nwPacketBurstIOPerSec
nwPacketBurstIOPerSec.description: Packet Burst IO/sec is the sum of Packet Burst Read NCPs/sec and Packet Burst Write NCPs/sec.

nwPacketBurstReadNCPCountPerSec.name: nwPacketBurstReadNCPCountPerSec
nwPacketBurstReadNCPCountPerSec.description: Packet Burst Read NCP Count/sec is the rate of NetWare Core Protocol requests for Packet Burst Read. Packet Burst is a windowing protocol that improves performance.

nwPacketBurstReadTimeoutsPerSec.name: nwPacketBurstReadTimeoutsPerSec
nwPacketBurstReadTimeoutsPerSec.description: Packet Burst Read Timeouts/sec is the rate the NetWare Service needs to retransmit a Burst Read Request because the NetWare server took too long to respond.

nwPacketBurstWriteNCPCountPerSec.name: nwPacketBurstWriteNCPCountPerSec
nwPacketBurstWriteNCPCountPerSec.description: Packet Burst Write NCP Count/sec is the rate of NetWare Core Protocol requests for Packet Burst Write. Packet Burst is a windowing protocol that improves performance.

nwPacketBurstWriteTimeoutsPerSec.name: nwPacketBurstWriteTimeoutsPerSec
nwPacketBurstWriteTimeoutsPerSec.description: Packet Burst Write Timeouts/sec is the rate the NetWare Service needs to retransmit a Burst Write Request because the NetWare server took too long to respond.

nwPacketsReceivedPerSec.name: nwPacketsReceivedPerSec
nwPacketsReceivedPerSec.description: Packets Received/sec is the rate at which the Redirector is receiving packets (also called SMBs or Server Message Blocks). Network transmissions are divided into packets. The average number of bytes received in a packet can be obtained by dividing Bytes Received/sec by this counter. Some packets received might not contain incoming data, for example an acknowledgment to a write made by the Redirector would count as an incoming packet.

nwPacketsTransmittedPerSec.name: nwPacketsTransmittedPerSec
nwPacketsTransmittedPerSec.description: Packets Transmitted/sec is the rate at which the Redirector is sending packets (also called SMBs or Server Message Blocks). Network transmissions are divided into packets. The average number of bytes transmitted in a packet can be obtained by dividing Bytes Transmitted/sec by this counter.

nwPacketsPerSec.name: nwPacketsPerSec
nwPacketsPerSec.description: Packets/sec is the rate the Redirector is processing data packets. One packet includes (hopefully) many bytes. We say hopefully here because each packet has protocol overhead. You can determine the efficiency of this path by dividing the Bytes/sec by this counter to determine the average number of bytes transferred/packet. You can also divide this counter by Operations/sec to determine the average number of packets per operation, another measure of efficiency.

nwReadOperationsRandomPerSec.name: nwReadOperationsRandomPerSec
nwReadOperationsRandomPerSec.description: Read Operations Random/sec counts the rate at which, on a file-by-file basis, reads are made that are not sequential. If a read is made using a particular file handle, and then is followed by another read that is not immediately the contiguous next byte, this counter is incremented by one.

nwReadPacketsPerSec.name: nwReadPacketsPerSec
nwReadPacketsPerSec.description: Read Packets/sec is the rate at which read packets are being placed on the network. Each time a single packet is sent with a request to read data remotely, this counter is incremented by one.

nwServerDisconnects.name: nwServerDisconnects
nwServerDisconnects.description: Server Disconnects counts the number of times a Server has disconnected your Redirector. See also Server Reconnects.

nwServerReconnects.name: nwServerReconnects
nwServerReconnects.description: Server Reconnects counts the number of times your Redirector has had to reconnect to a server in order to complete a new active request. You can be disconnected by the Server if you remain inactive for too long. Locally even if all your remote files are closed, the Redirector will keep your connections intact for (nominally) ten minutes. Such inactive connections are called Dormant Connections. Reconnecting is expensive in time.

nwServerSessions.name: nwServerSessions
nwServerSessions.description: Server Sessions counts the total number of security objects the Redirector has managed. For example, a logon to a server followed by a network access to the same server will establish one connection, but two sessions.

nwWriteOperationsRandomPerSec.name: nwWriteOperationsRandomPerSec
nwWriteOperationsRandomPerSec.description: Write Operations Random/sec is the rate at which, on a file-by-file basis, writes are made that are not sequential. If a write is made using a particular file handle, and then is followed by another write that is not immediately the next contiguous byte, this counter is incremented by one.

nwWritePacketsPerSec.name: nwWritePacketsPerSec
nwWritePacketsPerSec.description: Write Packets/sec is the rate at which writes are being sent to the network. Each time a single packet is sent with a request to write remote data, this counter is incremented by one.

iasAccountingClientsTable.name: iasAccountingClientsTable
iasAccountingClientsTable.description: The IAS Accounting Clients performance object is installed by the Internet Authentication Service (IAS). IAS uses the Remote Authentication Dial-In User Service (RADIUS) protocol to perform remote authentication. IAS performance objects report activity for servers or clients, including user authentication, authorization, and accounting (usage).

iasAccountingClientsEntry.name: iasAccountingClientsEntry
iasAccountingClientsEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'IAS Accounting Clients' object.

iccAccountingRequests.name: iccAccountingRequests
iccAccountingRequests.description: Shows the number of packets received from this client on the accounting port.

iccAccountingRequestsPerSec.name: iccAccountingRequestsPerSec
iccAccountingRequestsPerSec.description: Shows the rate, in seconds, at which packets were received from this client on the accounting port.

iccAccountingResponses.name: iccAccountingResponses
iccAccountingResponses.description: Shows the number of RADIUS Accounting-Response packets sent to this client.

iccAccountingResponsesPerSec.name: iccAccountingResponsesPerSec
iccAccountingResponsesPerSec.description: Shows the rate in seconds at which duplicate RADIUS Accounting-Request packets were received from this client.

iccBadAuthenticators.name: iccBadAuthenticators
iccBadAuthenticators.description: Shows the number of packets that contained invalid Signature attributes.

iccBadAuthenticatorsPerSec.name: iccBadAuthenticatorsPerSec
iccBadAuthenticatorsPerSec.description: Shows the rate, in seconds, at which packets that contained invalid Signature attributes were received.

iccDroppedPackets.name: iccDroppedPackets
iccDroppedPackets.description: Shows the number of incoming packets silently discarded for a reason other than being malformed, bad authenticators, or unknown types.

iccDroppedPacketsPerSec.name: iccDroppedPacketsPerSec
iccDroppedPacketsPerSec.description: Shows the rate in seconds at which incoming packets were silently discarded for a reason other than being malformed, bad authenticators, or unknown types.

iccDuplicateAccountingRequests.name: iccDuplicateAccountingRequests
iccDuplicateAccountingRequests.description: Shows the number of duplicate RADIUS Accounting-Request packets received from this client.

iccDuplicateAccountingRqstPerSec.name: iccDuplicateAccountingRqstPerSec
iccDuplicateAccountingRqstPerSec.description: Shows the rate, in seconds, at which duplicate RADIUS Accounting-Request packets were received from this client.

iccMalformedPackets.name: iccMalformedPackets
iccMalformedPackets.description: Shows the number of malformed packets received. Bad authenticators or unknown types are not included.

iccMalformedPacketsPerSec.name: iccMalformedPacketsPerSec
iccMalformedPacketsPerSec.description: Shows the rate, in seconds, at which malformed packets were received.

iccNoRecord.name: iccNoRecord
iccNoRecord.description: Shows the number of RADIUS Accounting-Request packets that were received and responded to but not recorded.

iccNoRecordPerSec.name: iccNoRecordPerSec
iccNoRecordPerSec.description: Shows the rate, in seconds, at which RADIUS Accounting-Request packets were received and responded to but not recorded.

iccPacketsReceived.name: iccPacketsReceived
iccPacketsReceived.description: Shows the number of packets received.

iccPacketsReceivedPerSec.name: iccPacketsReceivedPerSec
iccPacketsReceivedPerSec.description: Shows the rate, in seconds, at which packets were received.

iccPacketsSent.name: iccPacketsSent
iccPacketsSent.description: Shows the number of packets sent.

iccPacketsSentPerSec.name: iccPacketsSentPerSec
iccPacketsSentPerSec.description: Shows the rate, in seconds, at which packets were sent.

iccUnknownType.name: iccUnknownType
iccUnknownType.description: Shows the number of packets of unknown type that were received. An unknown type is a RADIUS packet that contains an unrecognized entry in the Code field, used to identify the packet type. Consequently IAS does not support packets of unknown type.

iccUnknownTypePerSec.name: iccUnknownTypePerSec
iccUnknownTypePerSec.description: Shows the rate, in seconds, at which packets of unknown type were received.

icpAccountingRequestsPerSec.name: icpAccountingRequestsPerSec
icpAccountingRequestsPerSec.description: The average number of RADIUS Accounting-Request packets sent per second to the accounting port.

icpAccountingResponsesPerSec.description: The average number of RADIUS Accounting-Response packets received per second on the accounting port.

icpBadAuthenticatorsPerSec.description: The average number of RADIUS packets per second that contain an invalid Message Authenticator attribute.

icpMalformedPacketsPerSec.description: The average number of packets containing malformed data received per second.

icpPacketsReceivedPerSec.name: icpPacketsReceivedPerSec
icpPacketsReceivedPerSec.description: The average number of packets received per second.

icpPendingRequests.name: icpPendingRequests
icpPendingRequests.description: The number of requests destined for this server that have not yet timed out or received a response.

icpRequestTimeouts.name: icpRequestTimeouts
icpRequestTimeouts.description: The number of request timeouts to this server.

icpRequestTimeoutsPerSec.name: icpRequestTimeoutsPerSec
icpRequestTimeoutsPerSec.description: The average number of request timeouts per second to this server.

icpRetransmissions.name: icpRetransmissions

icmpV4.name: icmpV4
icmpV4.description: The ICMP performance object consists of counters that measure the rates at which Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) messages are sent and received by using the ICMP protocol. It also includes counters that monitor ICMP protocol errors.

icmpV4MessagesOutboundErrors.name: icmpV4MessagesOutboundErrors
icmpV4MessagesOutboundErrors.description: Messages Outbound Errors is the number of ICMP messages that were not send due to problems within ICMP, such as lack of buffers. This value does not include errors discovered outside the ICMP layer, such as those recording the failure of IP to route the resultant datagram. In some implementations, none of the error types are included in the value of this counter.

icmpV4MessagesReceivedErrors.name: icmpV4MessagesReceivedErrors
icmpV4MessagesReceivedErrors.description: Messages Received Errors is the number of ICMP messages that the entity received but had errors, such as bad ICMP checksums, bad length, etc.

icmpV4MessagesReceivedPerSec.name: icmpV4MessagesReceivedPerSec
icmpV4MessagesReceivedPerSec.description: Messages Received/sec is the rate, in incidents per second at which ICMP messages were received. The rate includes messages received in error.

icmpV4MessagesSentPerSec.name: icmpV4MessagesSentPerSec
icmpV4MessagesSentPerSec.description: Messages Sent/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which the server attempted to send. The rate includes those messages sent in error.

icmpV4MessagesPerSec.name: icmpV4MessagesPerSec
icmpV4MessagesPerSec.description: Messages/sec is the total rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP messages were sent and received by the entity. The rate includes messages received or sent in error.

icmpV4RcvdAddressMask.name: icmpV4RcvdAddressMask
icmpV4RcvdAddressMask.description: Received Address Mask is the number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages received.

icmpV4RcvdAddressMaskReply.name: icmpV4RcvdAddressMaskReply
icmpV4RcvdAddressMaskReply.description: Received Address Mask Reply is the number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages received.

icmpV4RcvdDestUnreachable.name: icmpV4RcvdDestUnreachable
icmpV4RcvdDestUnreachable.description: Received Destination Unreachable is the number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages received.

icmpV4RcvdEchoReplyPerSec.name: icmpV4RcvdEchoReplyPerSec
icmpV4RcvdEchoReplyPerSec.description: Received Echo Reply/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Echo Reply messages were received.

icmpV4RcvdEchoPerSec.name: icmpV4RcvdEchoPerSec
icmpV4RcvdEchoPerSec.description: Received Echo/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Echo messages were received.

icmpV4RcvdParameterProblem.name: icmpV4RcvdParameterProblem
icmpV4RcvdParameterProblem.description: Received Parameter Problem is the number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages received.

icmpV4RcvdRedirectPerSec.name: icmpV4RcvdRedirectPerSec
icmpV4RcvdRedirectPerSec.description: Received Redirect/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Redirect messages were received.

icmpV4RcvdSourceQuench.name: icmpV4RcvdSourceQuench
icmpV4RcvdSourceQuench.description: Received Source Quench is the number of ICMP Source Quench messages received.

icmpV4RcvdTimeExceeded.name: icmpV4RcvdTimeExceeded
icmpV4RcvdTimeExceeded.description: Received Time Exceeded is the number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages received.

icmpV4RcvdTimestampReplyPerSec.name: icmpV4RcvdTimestampReplyPerSec
icmpV4RcvdTimestampReplyPerSec.description: Received Timestamp Reply/sec is the rate of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages received.

icmpV4RcvdTimestampPerSec.name: icmpV4RcvdTimestampPerSec
icmpV4RcvdTimestampPerSec.description: Received Timestamp/sec is the rate, in incidents per second at which ICMP Timestamp Request messages were received.

icmpV4SentAddressMask.name: icmpV4SentAddressMask
icmpV4SentAddressMask.description: Sent Address Mask is the number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages sent.

icmpV4SentAddressMaskReply.name: icmpV4SentAddressMaskReply
icmpV4SentAddressMaskReply.description: Sent Address Mask Reply is the number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages sent.

icmpV4SentDestinationUnreachable.name: icmpV4SentDestinationUnreachable
icmpV4SentDestinationUnreachable.description: Sent Destination Unreachable is the number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages sent.

icmpV4SentEchoReplyPerSec.name: icmpV4SentEchoReplyPerSec
icmpV4SentEchoReplyPerSec.description: Sent Echo Reply/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Echo Reply messages were sent.

icmpV4SentEchoPerSec.name: icmpV4SentEchoPerSec
icmpV4SentEchoPerSec.description: Sent Echo/sec is the rate of ICMP Echo messages sent.

icmpV4SentParameterProblem.name: icmpV4SentParameterProblem
icmpV4SentParameterProblem.description: Sent Parameter Problem is the number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages sent.

icmpV4SentRedirectPerSec.name: icmpV4SentRedirectPerSec
icmpV4SentRedirectPerSec.description: Sent Redirect/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Redirect messages were sent.

icmpV4SentSourceQuench.name: icmpV4SentSourceQuench
icmpV4SentSourceQuench.description: Sent Source Quench is the number of ICMP Source Quench messages sent.

icmpV4SentTimeExceeded.name: icmpV4SentTimeExceeded
icmpV4SentTimeExceeded.description: Sent Time Exceeded is the number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages sent.

icmpV4SentTimestampReplyPerSec.name: icmpV4SentTimestampReplyPerSec
icmpV4SentTimestampReplyPerSec.description: Sent Timestamp Reply/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Timestamp Reply messages were sent.

icmpV4SentTimestampPerSec.name: icmpV4SentTimestampPerSec
icmpV4SentTimestampPerSec.description: Sent Timestamp/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Timestamp Request messages were sent.

icmpV6MessagesOutboundErrors.name: icmpV6MessagesOutboundErrors
icmpV6MessagesOutboundErrors.description: Messages Outbound Errors is the number of ICMP messages that were not send due to problems within ICMP, such as lack of buffers. This value does not include errors discovered outside the ICMP layer, such as those recording the failure of IP to route the resultant datagram. In some implementations, none of the error types are included in the value of this counter.

icmpV6MessagesReceivedErrors.name: icmpV6MessagesReceivedErrors
icmpV6MessagesReceivedErrors.description: Messages Received Errors is the number of ICMP messages that the entity received but had errors, such as bad ICMP checksums, bad length, etc.

icmpV6MessagesReceivedPerSec.name: icmpV6MessagesReceivedPerSec
icmpV6MessagesReceivedPerSec.description: Messages Received/sec is the rate, in incidents per second at which ICMP messages were received. The rate includes messages received in error.

icmpV6MessagesSentPerSec.name: icmpV6MessagesSentPerSec
icmpV6MessagesSentPerSec.description: Messages Sent/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which the server attempted to send. The rate includes those messages sent in error.

icmpV6MessagesPerSec.name: icmpV6MessagesPerSec
icmpV6MessagesPerSec.description: Messages/sec is the total rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP messages were sent and received by the entity. The rate includes messages received or sent in error.

icmpV6ReceivedDestUnreachable.name: icmpV6ReceivedDestUnreachable
icmpV6ReceivedDestUnreachable.description: Received Destination Unreachable is the number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages received.

icmpV6ReceivedEchoReplyPerSec.name: icmpV6ReceivedEchoReplyPerSec
icmpV6ReceivedEchoReplyPerSec.description: Received Echo Reply/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Echo Reply messages were received.

icmpV6ReceivedEchoPerSec.name: icmpV6ReceivedEchoPerSec
icmpV6ReceivedEchoPerSec.description: Received Echo/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Echo messages were received.

icmpV6ReceivedMembershipQuery.name: icmpV6ReceivedMembershipQuery
icmpV6ReceivedMembershipQuery.description: Received Membership Query is the number of packets received thatquery their membership to a group.

icmpV6ReceivedMembershipReduct.name: icmpV6ReceivedMembershipReduct
icmpV6ReceivedMembershipReduct.description: Received Membership Reduction is the number of packets received thatcancelled their membership to a group.

icmpV6ReceivedMembershipReport.name: icmpV6ReceivedMembershipReport

icmpV6ReceivedRedirectPerSec.name: icmpV6ReceivedRedirectPerSec
icmpV6ReceivedRedirectPerSec.description: Received Redirect/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Redirect messages were received.

icmpV6ReceivedRouterAdvert.name: icmpV6ReceivedRouterAdvert
icmpV6ReceivedRouterAdvert.description: Received Router Advert is the number of packets received thatadvert the router.

icmpV6ReceivedRouterSolicit.name: icmpV6ReceivedRouterSolicit

icmpV6ReceivedTimeExceeded.name: icmpV6ReceivedTimeExceeded
icmpV6ReceivedTimeExceeded.description: Received Time Exceeded is the number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages received.

icmpV6SentDestinationUnreachable.name: icmpV6SentDestinationUnreachable
icmpV6SentDestinationUnreachable.description: Sent Destination Unreachable is the number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages sent.

icmpV6SentEchoReplyPerSec.name: icmpV6SentEchoReplyPerSec
icmpV6SentEchoReplyPerSec.description: Sent Echo Reply/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which ICMP Echo Reply messages were sent.

icmpV6SentEchoPerSec.name: icmpV6SentEchoPerSec
icmpV6SentEchoPerSec.description: Sent Echo/sec is the rate of ICMP Echo messages sent.

icmpV6SentMembershipQuery.name: icmpV6SentMembershipQuery
icmpV6SentMembershipQuery.description: Sent Membership Query is the number of packets sent thatquery their membership to a group.

icmpV6SentMembershipReduction.name: icmpV6SentMembershipReduction

icmpV6SentMembershipReport.name: icmpV6SentMembershipReport

icmpV6SentNeighborAdvert.name: icmpV6SentNeighborAdvert

icmpV6SentNeighborSolicit.name: icmpV6SentNeighborSolicit

indexingServiceTable.description: The Indexing Service performance object counters report statistics pertaining to the creation of indexes and the merging and querying of indexes by Indexing Service.

indexingServiceEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'Indexing Service' object.

idxSvcNumDocumentsIndexed.description: Number of documents indexed since the index was mounted.

idxSvcDeferredForIndexing.name: idxSvcDeferredForIndexing
idxSvcDeferredForIndexing.description: Number of files not available and deferred for indexing.

idxSvcFilesToBeIndexed.name: idxSvcFilesToBeIndexed
idxSvcFilesToBeIndexed.description: Number of files to be filtered and added to the index.

idxSvcIndexSizeMB.name: idxSvcIndexSizeMB
idxSvcIndexSizeMB.description: Size of the content index (*.ci files only) in megabytes.

idxSvcMergeProgress.name: idxSvcMergeProgress
idxSvcMergeProgress.description: Percent merge complete for the current merge.

idxSvcRunningQueries.name: idxSvcRunningQueries
idxSvcRunningQueries.description: Number of active query client connections.

idxSvcTotalNumDocuments.name: idxSvcTotalNumDocuments
idxSvcTotalNumDocuments.description: Total number of documents in the index.

idxSvcTotalNumOfQueries.name: idxSvcTotalNumOfQueries
idxSvcTotalNumOfQueries.description: Total number of queries since the index was mounted.

idxSvcUniqueKeys.name: idxSvcUniqueKeys
idxSvcUniqueKeys.description: Number of unique keys (words, etc.) in the index.

indexingServiceFilterTable.name: indexingServiceFilterTable
indexingServiceFilterTable.description: The Index Service Filter object monitors the filtering activity of Indexing Service.

indexingServiceFilterEntry.name: indexingServiceFilterEntry
indexingServiceFilterEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'Indexing Service Filter' object.

idxSvcFilterBindingTimeMsec.name: idxSvcFilterBindingTimeMsec
idxSvcFilterBindingTimeMsec.description: Average time spent binding to indexing filters.

idxSvcFilterIdxSpeedMBPerHr.name: idxSvcFilterIdxSpeedMBPerHr
idxSvcFilterIdxSpeedMBPerHr.description: Speed of indexing contents of files in megabytes per hour.

idxSvcFilterTotalIdxSpeedMBPerHr.name: idxSvcFilterTotalIdxSpeedMBPerHr
idxSvcFilterTotalIdxSpeedMBPerHr.description: Speed of indexing file contents and properties in megabytes per hour.

internetInformationServiceGlobal.name: internetInformationServiceGlobal
internetInformationServiceGlobal.description: The Internet Information Services Global performance object consists of counters that apply jointly to the Hypertext Transport Protocol (HTTP) service and File Transfer Protocol (FTP) service.

iisGlobalActiveFlushedEntries.name: iisGlobalActiveFlushedEntries
iisGlobalActiveFlushedEntries.description: Active Flushed Entries are cached file handles that will be closed when all current transfers complete.

iisGlobalBLOBCacheFlushes.name: iisGlobalBLOBCacheFlushes
iisGlobalBLOBCacheFlushes.description: BLOB Cache Flushes since server startup.

iisGlobalBLOBCacheHits.name: iisGlobalBLOBCacheHits
iisGlobalBLOBCacheHits.description: Total number of successful lookups in the BLOB cache.

iisGlobalBLOBCacheHitsPercent.name: iisGlobalBLOBCacheHitsPercent
iisGlobalBLOBCacheHitsPercent.description: The ratio of BLOB Cache Hits to total cache requests.

iisGlobalBLOBCacheMisses.name: iisGlobalBLOBCacheMisses
iisGlobalBLOBCacheMisses.description: Total number of unsuccessful lookups in the BLOB cache.

iisGlobalCurBLOBsCached.name: iisGlobalCurBLOBsCached
iisGlobalCurBLOBsCached.description: BLOB information blocks currently in the cache for WWW and FTP services.

iisGlobalCurBlockAsyncIORequests.name: iisGlobalCurBlockAsyncIORequests
iisGlobalCurBlockAsyncIORequests.description: Current requests temporarily blocked due to bandwidth throttling settings.

iisGlobalCurFileCacheMemUsage.name: iisGlobalCurFileCacheMemUsage
iisGlobalCurFileCacheMemUsage.description: Current number of bytes used for file cache.

iisGlobalCurFilesCached.name: iisGlobalCurFilesCached
iisGlobalCurFilesCached.description: Current number of files whose content is in the cache for WWW and FTP services.

iisGlobalCurURIsCached.name: iisGlobalCurURIsCached
iisGlobalCurURIsCached.description: URI information blocks currently in the cache for WWW and FTP services.

iisGlobalFileCacheFlushes.name: iisGlobalFileCacheFlushes
iisGlobalFileCacheFlushes.description: File Cache Flushes since server startup.

iisGlobalFileCacheHits.name: iisGlobalFileCacheHits
iisGlobalFileCacheHits.description: Total number of successful lookups in the file cache.

iisGlobalFileCacheHitsPercent.name: iisGlobalFileCacheHitsPercent
iisGlobalFileCacheHitsPercent.description: The ratio of File Cache Hits to total cache requests.

iisGlobalFileCacheMisses.name: iisGlobalFileCacheMisses
iisGlobalFileCacheMisses.description: Total number of unsuccessful lookups in the file cache.

iisGlobalMaxFileCacheMemUsage.name: iisGlobalMaxFileCacheMemUsage
iisGlobalMaxFileCacheMemUsage.description: Maximum number of bytes used for file cache.

iisGlobalMeasuredAsyncIOBwUsage.name: iisGlobalMeasuredAsyncIOBwUsage
iisGlobalMeasuredAsyncIOBwUsage.description: Measured bandwidth of asynchronous I/O averaged over a minute.

iisGlobalTotalAllowedAsyncIOReqs.name: iisGlobalTotalAllowedAsyncIOReqs
iisGlobalTotalAllowedAsyncIOReqs.description: Total requests allowed by bandwidth throttling settings (counted since service startup).

iisGlobalTotalBLOBsCached.name: iisGlobalTotalBLOBsCached
iisGlobalTotalBLOBsCached.description: Total number of BLOB information blocks ever added to the cache for WWW and FTP services

iisGlobalTotalBlockAsyncIOReqs.name: iisGlobalTotalBlockAsyncIOReqs
iisGlobalTotalBlockAsyncIOReqs.description: Total requests temporarily blocked due to bandwidth throttling settings (counted since service startup).

iisGlobalTotalFilesCached.name: iisGlobalTotalFilesCached
iisGlobalTotalFilesCached.description: Total number of files whose content was ever added to the cache for WWW and FTP services

iisGlobalTotalFlushedBLOBs.name: iisGlobalTotalFlushedBLOBs
iisGlobalTotalFlushedBLOBs.description: Total Flushed BLOBs is the number of BLOB information blocks that have been removed from the cache since service start up.

iisGlobalTotalFlushedFiles.name: iisGlobalTotalFlushedFiles
iisGlobalTotalFlushedFiles.description: Total Flushed Files is the number of file handles that have been removed from the cache since service start up.

iisGlobalTotalFlushedURIs.name: iisGlobalTotalFlushedURIs

ipV4.name: ipV4
ipV4.description: The Internet Protocol (IP) performance object includes counters that describe the rates at which IP datagrams are transmitted by a computer using the IP protocol. It also describes various error counts for the IP protocol.

ipV4DatagramsForwardedPerSec.name: ipV4DatagramsForwardedPerSec
ipV4DatagramsForwardedPerSec.description: Datagrams Forwarded/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which attemps were made to find routes to forward input datagrams their final destination, because the local server was not the final IP destination. In servers that do not act as IP Gateways, this rate includes only packets that were source-routed via this entity, where the source-route option processing was successful.

ipV4DatagramsOutboundDiscarded.name: ipV4DatagramsOutboundDiscarded
ipV4DatagramsOutboundDiscarded.description: Datagrams Outbound Discarded is the number of output IP datagrams that were discarded even though no problems were encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination (for example, lack of buffer space). This counter includes datagrams counted in Datagrams Forwarded/sec that meet this criterion.

ipV4DatagramsOutboundNoRoute.name: ipV4DatagramsOutboundNoRoute
ipV4DatagramsOutboundNoRoute.description: Datagrams Outbound No Route is the number of IP datagrams that were discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. This counter includes any packets counted in Datagrams Forwarded/sec that meet this `no route' criterion.

ipV4DatagramsRcvdAddressErrors.name: ipV4DatagramsRcvdAddressErrors
ipV4DatagramsRcvdAddressErrors.description: Datagrams Received Address Errors is the number of input datagrams that were discarded because the IP address in their IP header destination field was not valid for the computer. This count includes invalid addresses (for example, 0.0. 0.0) and addresses of unsupported Classes (for example, Class E). For entities that are not IP gateways and do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams that were discarded because the destination address was not a local address.

ipV4DatagramsRcvdDeliveredPerSec.name: ipV4DatagramsRcvdDeliveredPerSec
ipV4DatagramsRcvdDeliveredPerSec.description: Datagrams Received Delivered/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which input datagrams were successfully delivered to IP user-protocols, including Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP).

ipV4DatagramsRcvdDiscarded.name: ipV4DatagramsRcvdDiscarded
ipV4DatagramsRcvdDiscarded.description: Datagrams Received Discarded is the number of input IP datagrams that were discarded even though problems prevented their continued processing (for example, lack of buffer space). This counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly.

ipV4DatagramsRcvdHeaderErrors.name: ipV4DatagramsRcvdHeaderErrors
ipV4DatagramsRcvdHeaderErrors.description: Datagrams Received Header Errors is the number of input datagrams that were discarded due to errors in the IP headers, including bad checksums, version number mismatch, other format errors, time-to-live exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

ipV4DatagramsRcvdUnknownProtocol.name: ipV4DatagramsRcvdUnknownProtocol
ipV4DatagramsRcvdUnknownProtocol.description: Datagrams Received Unknown Protocol is the number of locally-addressed datagrams that were successfully received but were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

ipV4DatagramsRcvdPerSec.name: ipV4DatagramsRcvdPerSec
ipV4DatagramsRcvdPerSec.description: Datagrams Received/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP datagrams are received from the interfaces, including those in error. Datagrams Received/sec is a subset of Datagrams/sec.

ipV4DatagramsSentPerSec.name: ipV4DatagramsSentPerSec
ipV4DatagramsSentPerSec.description: Datagrams Sent/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP datagrams were supplied for transmission by local IP user-protocols (including ICMP). This counter does not include any datagrams counted in Datagrams Forwarded/sec. Datagrams Sent/sec is a subset of Datagrams/sec.

ipV4DatagramsPerSec.name: ipV4DatagramsPerSec
ipV4DatagramsPerSec.description: Datagrams/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP datagrams were received from or sent to the interfaces, including those in error. Forwarded datagrams are not included in this rate.

ipV4FragmentReassemblyFailures.name: ipV4FragmentReassemblyFailures
ipV4FragmentReassemblyFailures.description: Fragment Re-assembly Failures is the number of failures detected by the IP reassembly algorithm, such as time outs, errors, etc. This is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments since some algorithms (notably RFC 815) lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received.

ipV4FragmentationFailures.name: ipV4FragmentationFailures
ipV4FragmentationFailures.description: Fragmentation Failures is the number of IP datagrams that were discarded because they needed to be fragmented at but could not be (for example, because the `Don't Fragment' flag was set).

ipV4FragmentedDatagramsPerSec.name: ipV4FragmentedDatagramsPerSec
ipV4FragmentedDatagramsPerSec.description: Fragmented Datagrams/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which datagrams are successfully fragmented.

ipV4FragmentsCreatedPerSec.name: ipV4FragmentsCreatedPerSec
ipV4FragmentsCreatedPerSec.description: Fragments Created/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP datagram fragments were generated as a result of fragmentation.

ipV4FragmentsReassembledPerSec.name: ipV4FragmentsReassembledPerSec
ipV4FragmentsReassembledPerSec.description: Fragments Re-assembled/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP fragments were successfully reassembled.

ipV4FragmentsRcvdPerSec.name: ipV4FragmentsRcvdPerSec
ipV4FragmentsRcvdPerSec.description: Fragments Received/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP fragments that need to be reassembled at this entity are received.

ipV6DatagramsForwardedPerSec.name: ipV6DatagramsForwardedPerSec
ipV6DatagramsForwardedPerSec.description: Datagrams Forwarded/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which attemps were made to find routes to forward input datagrams their final destination, because the local server was not the final IP destination. In servers that do not act as IP Gateways, this rate includes only packets that were source-routed via this entity, where the source-route option processing was successful.

ipV6DatagramsOutboundDiscarded.name: ipV6DatagramsOutboundDiscarded
ipV6DatagramsOutboundDiscarded.description: Datagrams Outbound Discarded is the number of output IP datagrams that were discarded even though no problems were encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination (for example, lack of buffer space). This counter includes datagrams counted in Datagrams Forwarded/sec that meet this criterion.

ipV6DatagramsOutboundNoRoute.name: ipV6DatagramsOutboundNoRoute
ipV6DatagramsOutboundNoRoute.description: Datagrams Outbound No Route is the number of IP datagrams that were discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. This counter includes any packets counted in Datagrams Forwarded/sec that meet this `no route' criterion.

ipV6DatagramsRcvdAddressErrors.name: ipV6DatagramsRcvdAddressErrors
ipV6DatagramsRcvdAddressErrors.description: Datagrams Received Address Errors is the number of input datagrams that were discarded because the IP address in their IP header destination field was not valid for the computer. This count includes invalid addresses (for example, 0.0. 0.0) and addresses of unsupported Classes (for example, Class E). For entities that are not IP gateways and do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams that were discarded because the destination address was not a local address.

ipV6DatagramsRcvdDeliveredPerSec.name: ipV6DatagramsRcvdDeliveredPerSec
ipV6DatagramsRcvdDeliveredPerSec.description: Datagrams Received Delivered/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which input datagrams were successfully delivered to IP user-protocols, including Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP).

ipV6DatagramsRcvdDiscarded.name: ipV6DatagramsRcvdDiscarded
ipV6DatagramsRcvdDiscarded.description: Datagrams Received Discarded is the number of input IP datagrams that were discarded even though problems prevented their continued processing (for example, lack of buffer space). This counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly.

ipV6DatagramsRcvdHeaderErrors.name: ipV6DatagramsRcvdHeaderErrors
ipV6DatagramsRcvdHeaderErrors.description: Datagrams Received Header Errors is the number of input datagrams that were discarded due to errors in the IP headers, including bad checksums, version number mismatch, other format errors, time-to-live exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

ipV6DatagramsRcvdUnknownProtocol.name: ipV6DatagramsRcvdUnknownProtocol
ipV6DatagramsRcvdUnknownProtocol.description: Datagrams Received Unknown Protocol is the number of locally-addressed datagrams that were successfully received but were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

ipV6DatagramsRcvdPerSec.name: ipV6DatagramsRcvdPerSec
ipV6DatagramsRcvdPerSec.description: Datagrams Received/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP datagrams are received from the interfaces, including those in error. Datagrams Received/sec is a subset of Datagrams/sec.

ipV6DatagramsSentPerSec.name: ipV6DatagramsSentPerSec
ipV6DatagramsSentPerSec.description: Datagrams Sent/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP datagrams were supplied for transmission by local IP user-protocols (including ICMP). This counter does not include any datagrams counted in Datagrams Forwarded/sec. Datagrams Sent/sec is a subset of Datagrams/sec.

ipV6DatagramsPerSec.name: ipV6DatagramsPerSec
ipV6DatagramsPerSec.description: Datagrams/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP datagrams were received from or sent to the interfaces, including those in error. Forwarded datagrams are not included in this rate.

ipV6FragmentReassemblyFailures.name: ipV6FragmentReassemblyFailures
ipV6FragmentReassemblyFailures.description: Fragment Re-assembly Failures is the number of failures detected by the IP reassembly algorithm, such as time outs, errors, etc. This is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments since some algorithms (notably RFC 815) lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received.

ipV6FragmentationFailures.name: ipV6FragmentationFailures
ipV6FragmentationFailures.description: Fragmentation Failures is the number of IP datagrams that were discarded because they needed to be fragmented at but could not be (for example, because the `Don't Fragment' flag was set).

ipV6FragmentedDatagramsPerSec.name: ipV6FragmentedDatagramsPerSec
ipV6FragmentedDatagramsPerSec.description: Fragmented Datagrams/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which datagrams are successfully fragmented.

ipV6FragmentsCreatedPerSec.name: ipV6FragmentsCreatedPerSec
ipV6FragmentsCreatedPerSec.description: Fragments Created/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP datagram fragments were generated as a result of fragmentation.

ipV6FragmentsReassembledPerSec.name: ipV6FragmentsReassembledPerSec
ipV6FragmentsReassembledPerSec.description: Fragments Re-assembled/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP fragments were successfully reassembled.

ipV6FragmentsRcvdPerSec.name: ipV6FragmentsRcvdPerSec
ipV6FragmentsRcvdPerSec.description: Fragments Received/sec is the rate, in incidents per second, at which IP fragments that need to be reassembled at this entity are received.

is4dActiveSecurityAssociations.name: is4dActiveSecurityAssociations
is4dActiveSecurityAssociations.description: The number of active IPSec quick mode security associations.

is4dOffloadedSecurityAssociation.name: is4dOffloadedSecurityAssociation
is4dOffloadedSecurityAssociation.description: The number of active IPSec quick mode security associations offloaded to hardware. Certain network adapters can accelerate IPSec processing by performing hardware offload of IPSec cryptographic functions.

is4dPendingKeyExchangeOperations.name: is4dPendingKeyExchangeOperations
is4dPendingKeyExchangeOperations.description: The number of IPSec key exchange operations that are in progress but are not yet completed.

is4dTotalBadSPIPackets.name: is4dTotalBadSPIPackets
is4dTotalBadSPIPackets.description: The total number of packets for which the Security Parameters Index (SPI) was incorrect since the computer was last started. A large number of packets with bad SPIs within a short amount of time might indicate a packet spoofing attack.

is4dTotalBytesReceivedInTunnels.name: is4dTotalBytesReceivedInTunnels
is4dTotalBytesReceivedInTunnels.description: The total number of bytes received using IPSec tunnel mode since the computer was last started.

is4dTotalBytesSentInTunnels.name: is4dTotalBytesSentInTunnels
is4dTotalBytesSentInTunnels.description: The total number of bytes sent using IPSec tunnel mode since the computer was last started.

is4dTotalOffloadedBytesReceived.name: is4dTotalOffloadedBytesReceived
is4dTotalOffloadedBytesReceived.description: The total number of bytes received using IPSec hardware offload since the computer was last started. Certain network adapters can accelerate IPSec processing by performing hardware offload of IPSec cryptographic functions.

is4dTotalOffloadedBytesSent.name: is4dTotalOffloadedBytesSent
is4dTotalOffloadedBytesSent.description: The total number of bytes sent using IPSec hardware offload since the computer was last started. Certain network adapters can accelerate IPSec processing by performing hardware offload of IPSec cryptographic functions.

is4dTotalPktsFailReplayDetection.name: is4dTotalPktsFailReplayDetection
is4dTotalPktsFailReplayDetection.description: The total number of packets that contained an invalid sequence number since the computer was last started. Increases in this counter might indicate a network problem or replay attack.

is4dTotalPktsNotAuthenticated.name: is4dTotalPktsNotAuthenticated
is4dTotalPktsNotAuthenticated.description: The total number of packets for which data could not be verified (for which the integrity hash verification failed) since the computer was last started. Increases in this counter might indicate an IPSec packet spoofing or modification attack, or packet corruption by network devices.

is4dTotalPktsNotDecrypted.name: is4dTotalPktsNotDecrypted
is4dTotalPktsNotDecrypted.description: The total number of packets that could not be decrypted since the computer was last started. A packet might not be decrypted if it fails a validation check.

is4dTotalSARekeys.name: is4dTotalSARekeys
is4dTotalSARekeys.description: The total number of successful rekey operations for IPSec quick mode security associations since the computer was last started.

is4dTotalTransportBytesReceived.name: is4dTotalTransportBytesReceived
is4dTotalTransportBytesReceived.description: The total number of bytes received using IPSec transport mode since the computer was last started.

is4dTotalTransportBytesSent.name: is4dTotalTransportBytesSent
is4dTotalTransportBytesSent.description: The total number of bytes sent using IPSec transport mode since the computer was last started.

ipSecV4IKE.name: ipSecV4IKE
ipSecV4IKE.description: IPsec IKEv4 is the set of Internet Protocol security (IPsec) Internet Key Exchange (IKE) counters that apply to traffic and connections over Internet Protocol version 4.

is4iAcquireHeapSize.name: is4iAcquireHeapSize
is4iAcquireHeapSize.description: The number of entries in the acquire heap. The acquire heap stores successful acquires. Acquires are outbound requests to establish security associations between IPSec peers.

is4iMainModeSAListEntries.name: is4iMainModeSAListEntries
is4iMainModeSAListEntries.description: The number of main mode state entries. This counter includes successfully negotiated main modes, main mode negotiations in progress, and main mode negotiations that failed or expired and have not yet been deleted.

is4iQuickModeSAListEntries.name: is4iQuickModeSAListEntries
is4iQuickModeSAListEntries.description: The number of quick mode negotiations that are in progress.

is4iReceiveHeapSize.name: is4iReceiveHeapSize
is4iReceiveHeapSize.description: The number of entries in the Internet Key Exchange (IKE) receive buffers. The receive buffers are used to store incoming IKE messages.

is4iTotalAuthenticationFailures.name: is4iTotalAuthenticationFailures
is4iTotalAuthenticationFailures.description: The total number of identity authentication (Kerberos, certificate, and preshared key) failures that occurred during main mode negotiation since the IPSec service was last started.

is4iTotalMainModeSAs.name: is4iTotalMainModeSAs
is4iTotalMainModeSAs.description: The total number of successful security associations created during main mode negotiations since the IPSec service was last started.

is4iTotalNegotiationFailures.name: is4iTotalNegotiationFailures
is4iTotalNegotiationFailures.description: The total number of negotiation failures that occurred during main mode or quick mode negotiation since the IPSec service was last started.

is4iTotalQuickModeSAs.name: is4iTotalQuickModeSAs
is4iTotalQuickModeSAs.description: The total number of successful security associations created during quick mode negotiations since the IPSec service was last started.

is4iTotalSoftAssociations.name: is4iTotalSoftAssociations
is4iTotalSoftAssociations.description: The total number of security associations (SAs) formed with computers that did not respond to main mode negotiation attempts (though IPSec policy allowed communications) since the IPSec service was last started. Packets that match soft SAs are not secured by IPSec.

jobObjectTable.name: jobObjectTable
jobObjectTable.description: The Job performance object reports the accounting and processor usage data collected by each active job object. A job object provides a means of managing groups of processes with respect to their processor usage and other factors. For more information about creating and managing job objects, see the Platform SDK link on the Web Resources page at http://windows.microsoft.com/windows2000/reskit /webresources.

jobObjectEntry.name: jobObjectEntry
jobObjectEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'Job Object' object.

joCurrentPercentKernelModeTime.name: joCurrentPercentKernelModeTime
joCurrentPercentKernelModeTime.description: Current % Kernel mode Time shows the percentage of the sample interval that the processes in the Job object spent executing code in kernel or privileged mode.

joCurrentPercentProcessorTime.name: joCurrentPercentProcessorTime
joCurrentPercentProcessorTime.description: Current % Processor Time shows the percentage of the sample interval that the processes in the Job object spent executing code.

joCurrentPercentUserModeTime.name: joCurrentPercentUserModeTime
joCurrentPercentUserModeTime.description: Current % User mode Time shows the percentage of the sample interval that the processes in the Job object spent executing code in user mode.

joPagesPerSec.name: joPagesPerSec
joPagesPerSec.description: Pages/Sec shows the page fault rate of all the processes in the Job object.

joProcessCountActive.name: joProcessCountActive
joProcessCountActive.description: Process Count - Active shows the number of processes that are currently associated with the Job object.

joProcessCountTerminated.name: joProcessCountTerminated
joProcessCountTerminated.description: Process Count - Terminated shows the number of processes that have been terminated because of a limit violation.

joProcessCountTotal.name: joProcessCountTotal
joProcessCountTotal.description: Process Count - Total shows the number of processes, both active and terminated, that are or have been associated with the Job object.

joThisPeriodMSecKernelMode.name: joThisPeriodMSecKernelMode
joThisPeriodMSecKernelMode.description: This Period mSec - Kernel mode shows the time, in milliseconds, of kernel mode processor time used by all the processes in the Job object, including those that have terminated or that are no longer associated with the Job object, since a time limit on the Job was established.

joThisPeriodMSecProcessor.name: joThisPeriodMSecProcessor
joThisPeriodMSecProcessor.description: This Period mSec - Processor shows the time, in milliseconds, of processor time used by all the processes in the Job object, including those that have terminated or that are no longer associated with the Job object, since a time limit on the Job was established.

joThisPeriodMSecUserMode.name: joThisPeriodMSecUserMode
joThisPeriodMSecUserMode.description: This Period mSec - User mode shows the time, in milliseconds, of user mode processor time used by all the processes in the Job object, including those that have terminated or that are no longer associated with the Job object, since a time limit on the Job was established.

joTotalMSecKernelMode.name: joTotalMSecKernelMode
joTotalMSecKernelMode.description: Total mSec - Kernel mode shows the time, in milliseconds, of kernel mode processor time used by all the processes in the Job object, including those that have terminated or that are no longer associated with the Job object, since the Job object was created.

joTotalMSecProcessor.name: joTotalMSecProcessor
joTotalMSecProcessor.description: Total mSec - Processor shows the time, in milliseconds, of processor time used by all the processes in the Job object, including those that have terminated or that are no longer associated with the Job object, since the Job object was created.

joTotalMSecUserMode.name: joTotalMSecUserMode
joTotalMSecUserMode.description: Total mSec - User mode shows the time, in milliseconds, of user mode processor time used by all the processes in the Job object, including those that have terminated or that are no longer associated with the Job object, since the Job object was created.

jobObjectDetailsTable.name: jobObjectDetailsTable
