netCurrentBandwidth.description: Current Bandwidth is an estimate of the current bandwidth of the network interface in bits per second (BPS). For interfaces that do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this value is the nominal bandwidth.

netOutputQueueLength.name: netOutputQueueLength
netOutputQueueLength.description: Output Queue Length is the length of the output packet queue (in packets). If this is longer than two, there are delays and the bottleneck should be found and eliminated, if possible. Since the requests are queued by the Network Driver Interface Specification (NDIS) in this implementation, this will always be 0.

netPacketsOutboundDiscarded.name: netPacketsOutboundDiscarded
netPacketsOutboundDiscarded.description: Packets Outbound Discarded is the number of outbound packets that were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent transmission. One possible reason for discarding packets could be to free up buffer space.

netPacketsOutboundErrors.name: netPacketsOutboundErrors
netPacketsOutboundErrors.description: Packets Outbound Errors is the number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

netPacketsReceivedDiscarded.name: netPacketsReceivedDiscarded
netPacketsReceivedDiscarded.description: Packets Received Discarded is the number of inbound packets that were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their delivery to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding packets could be to free up buffer space.

netPacketsReceivedErrors.name: netPacketsReceivedErrors
netPacketsReceivedErrors.description: Packets Received Errors is the number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

netPacketsRcvdNonUnicastPerSec.name: netPacketsRcvdNonUnicastPerSec
netPacketsRcvdNonUnicastPerSec.description: Packets Received Non-Unicast/sec is the rate at which non-unicast (subnet broadcast or subnet multicast) packets are delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

netPacketsReceivedUnicastPerSec.name: netPacketsReceivedUnicastPerSec
netPacketsReceivedUnicastPerSec.description: Packets Received Unicast/sec is the rate at which (subnet) unicast packets are delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

netPacketsReceivedUnknown.name: netPacketsReceivedUnknown
netPacketsReceivedUnknown.description: Packets Received Unknown is the number of packets received through the interface that were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

netPacketsReceivedPerSec.name: netPacketsReceivedPerSec
netPacketsReceivedPerSec.description: Packets Received/sec is the rate at which packets are received on the network interface.

netPacketsSentNonUnicastPerSec.name: netPacketsSentNonUnicastPerSec
netPacketsSentNonUnicastPerSec.description: Packets Sent Non-Unicast/sec is the rate at which packets are requested to be transmitted to non-unicast (subnet broadcast or subnet multicast) addresses by higher-level protocols. The rate includes the packets that were discarded or not sent.

netPacketsSentUnicastPerSec.name: netPacketsSentUnicastPerSec
netPacketsSentUnicastPerSec.description: Packets Sent Unicast/sec is the rate at which packets are requested to be transmitted to subnet-unicast addresses by higher-level protocols. The rate includes the packets that were discarded or not sent.

netPacketsSentPerSec.name: netPacketsSentPerSec
netPacketsSentPerSec.description: Packets Sent/sec is the rate at which packets are sent on the network interface.

netPacketsPerSec.name: netPacketsPerSec
netPacketsPerSec.description: Packets/sec is the rate at which packets are sent and received on the network interface.

nntpCommandsTable.name: nntpCommandsTable
nntpCommandsTable.description: The NNTP Commands performance object includes counters for all NNTP commands processed by the Network News Transport Protocol (NNTP) service, which is installed as an optional component of Internet Information Services. NNTP counters are started for each virtual server instance and are reset to zero when the virtual server is started. A single NNTP service can have many virtual servers (also called sites).

nntpCommandsEntry.name: nntpCommandsEntry
nntpCommandsEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'NNTP Commands' object.

nntpCmdsArticleCmds.name: nntpCmdsArticleCmds
nntpCmdsArticleCmds.description: Article Commands is the number of ARTICLE commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsArticleCmdsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsArticleCmdsPerSec
nntpCmdsArticleCmdsPerSec.description: Article Commands/Sec is the number of ARTICLE commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsCheckCmds.name: nntpCmdsCheckCmds

nntpCmdsCheckCmdsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsCheckCmdsPerSec
nntpCmdsCheckCmdsPerSec.description: Check Commands/Sec is the number of CHECK commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsLastCmdsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsLastCmdsPerSec
nntpCmdsLastCmdsPerSec.description: Last Commands/Sec is the number of LAST commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsListCmds.name: nntpCmdsListCmds
nntpCmdsListCmds.description: List Commands is the number of LIST commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsListCmdsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsListCmdsPerSec
nntpCmdsListCmdsPerSec.description: List Commands/Sec is the number of LIST commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsLogonAttempts.name: nntpCmdsLogonAttempts
nntpCmdsLogonAttempts.description: Logon Attempts is the number of logon attempts that have been made to the NNTP Server.

nntpCmdsLogonAttemptsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsLogonAttemptsPerSec
nntpCmdsLogonAttemptsPerSec.description: Logon Attempts/Sec is the number of logon attempts per sec that have been made to the NNTP Server.

nntpCmdsLogonFailures.name: nntpCmdsLogonFailures
nntpCmdsLogonFailures.description: Logon Failures is the number of logons that had failed.

nntpCmdsLogonFailuresPerSec.name: nntpCmdsLogonFailuresPerSec
nntpCmdsLogonFailuresPerSec.description: Logon Failures/Sec is the number of logons per sec that had failed.

nntpCmdsModeCmds.name: nntpCmdsModeCmds
nntpCmdsModeCmds.description: Mode Commands is the number of MODE commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsModeCmdsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsModeCmdsPerSec
nntpCmdsModeCmdsPerSec.description: Mode Commands/Sec is the number of MODE commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsNewgroupsCmds.name: nntpCmdsNewgroupsCmds
nntpCmdsNewgroupsCmds.description: Newgroups Commands is the number of NEWGROUPS commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsNewgroupsCmdsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsNewgroupsCmdsPerSec
nntpCmdsNewgroupsCmdsPerSec.description: Newgroups Commands/Sec is the number of NEWGROUPS commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsNewnewsCmdsPerSec.description: Newnews Commands/Sec is the number of NEWNEWS commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsPostCmds.name: nntpCmdsPostCmds
nntpCmdsPostCmds.description: Post Commands is the number of POST commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsSearchCmds.name: nntpCmdsSearchCmds

nntpCmdsSearchCmdsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsSearchCmdsPerSec
nntpCmdsSearchCmdsPerSec.description: Search Commands/Sec is the number of SEARCH commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsStatCmdsPerSec.description: Stat Commands/Sec is the number of STAT commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsTakethisCmds.description: Takethis Commands is the number of TAKETHIS commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsTakethisCmdsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsTakethisCmdsPerSec
nntpCmdsTakethisCmdsPerSec.description: Takethis Commands/Sec is the number of TAKETHIS commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsXHdrCmds.name: nntpCmdsXHdrCmds
nntpCmdsXHdrCmds.description: XHdr Commands is the number of XHDR commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsXHdrCmdsPerSec.name: nntpCmdsXHdrCmdsPerSec
nntpCmdsXHdrCmdsPerSec.description: XHdr Commands/Sec is the number of XHDR commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsXOverCmds.name: nntpCmdsXOverCmds
nntpCmdsXOverCmds.description: XOver Commands is the number of XOVER commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsXOverCmdsPerSec.description: XOver Commands/Sec is the number of XOVER commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsXPatCmds.name: nntpCmdsXPatCmds
nntpCmdsXPatCmds.description: XPat Commands is the number of XPAT commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsXPatCmdsPerSec.description: XPat Commands/Sec is the number of XPAT commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsXReplicCmds.name: nntpCmdsXReplicCmds
nntpCmdsXReplicCmds.description: XReplic Commands is the number of XREPLIC commands received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpCmdsXReplicCmdsPerSec.description: XReplic Commands/Sec is the number of XREPLIC commands per sec received by the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpServerTable.name: nntpServerTable
nntpServerTable.description: The NNTP Server performance object monitors posting, authentication, and connection activity on an NNTP server. The Network News Transport Protocol (NNTP) service is an optional component of Internet Information Services. NNTP counters are started for each virtual server instance and are reset to zero when the virtual server is started. A single NNTP service can have many virtual servers (also called sites).

nntpServerEntry.name: nntpServerEntry
nntpServerEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'NNTP Server' object.

nntpSrvrArticleMapEntries.name: nntpSrvrArticleMapEntries
nntpSrvrArticleMapEntries.description: Article Map Entries is the entries inserted into the article mapping table of the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrArticleMapEntriesPerSec.name: nntpSrvrArticleMapEntriesPerSec
nntpSrvrArticleMapEntriesPerSec.description: Article Map Entries/Sec is the entries inserted per sec into the article mapping table of the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrArticlesDeleted.name: nntpSrvrArticlesDeleted
nntpSrvrArticlesDeleted.description: Articles Deleted is the number of articles deleted on the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpSrvrArticlesDeletedPerSec.name: nntpSrvrArticlesDeletedPerSec
nntpSrvrArticlesDeletedPerSec.description: Articles Deleted/Sec is the number of articles deleted per sec on the NNTP Server since it was started.

nntpSrvrArticlesPosted.name: nntpSrvrArticlesPosted
nntpSrvrArticlesPosted.description: Articles Posted is the number of articles posted to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrArticlesPostedPerSec.name: nntpSrvrArticlesPostedPerSec
nntpSrvrArticlesPostedPerSec.description: Articles Posted/Sec is the number of articles posted per sec to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrArticlesReceived.name: nntpSrvrArticlesReceived
nntpSrvrArticlesReceived.description: Articles Received is the total number of files received by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrArticlesReceivedPerSec.name: nntpSrvrArticlesReceivedPerSec
nntpSrvrArticlesReceivedPerSec.description: Articles Received/Sec is the total number of files per sec received by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrArticlesSent.name: nntpSrvrArticlesSent
nntpSrvrArticlesSent.description: Articles Sent is the total number of files sent by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrArticlesSentPerSec.name: nntpSrvrArticlesSentPerSec
nntpSrvrArticlesSentPerSec.description: Articles Sent/Sec is the total number of files sent per sec by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrArticlesTotal.name: nntpSrvrArticlesTotal
nntpSrvrArticlesTotal.description: Articles Total is the sum of Articles Sent and Articles Received. This is the total number of files transferred by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrBytesReceivedPerSec.name: nntpSrvrBytesReceivedPerSec
nntpSrvrBytesReceivedPerSec.description: Bytes Received/sec is the rate that data bytes are received by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrBytesSentPerSec.name: nntpSrvrBytesSentPerSec
nntpSrvrBytesSentPerSec.description: Bytes Sent/sec is the rate that data bytes are sent by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrBytesTotalPerSec.name: nntpSrvrBytesTotalPerSec
nntpSrvrBytesTotalPerSec.description: Bytes Total/sec is the sum of Bytes Sent/sec and Bytes Received/sec. This is the total rate of bytes transferred by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrControlMessagesFailed.name: nntpSrvrControlMessagesFailed
nntpSrvrControlMessagesFailed.description: Control Messages Failed is the total number of control messages failed or not applied by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrControlMessagesReceived.name: nntpSrvrControlMessagesReceived
nntpSrvrControlMessagesReceived.description: Control Messages Received is the total number of control messages received by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrCurrentAnonymousUsers.name: nntpSrvrCurrentAnonymousUsers
nntpSrvrCurrentAnonymousUsers.description: Current Anonymous Users is the number of anonymous users currently connected to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrCurrentConnections.name: nntpSrvrCurrentConnections
nntpSrvrCurrentConnections.description: Current Connections is the current number of connections to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrCurrentNonAnonymousUsers.name: nntpSrvrCurrentNonAnonymousUsers
nntpSrvrCurrentNonAnonymousUsers.description: Current NonAnonymous Users is the number of nonanonymous users currently connected to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrCurrentOutboundConns.name: nntpSrvrCurrentOutboundConns
nntpSrvrCurrentOutboundConns.description: Current Outbound Connections is the number of current outbound connections being made by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrFailedOutboundLogons.name: nntpSrvrFailedOutboundLogons
nntpSrvrFailedOutboundLogons.description: Failed Outbound Logons is the number of failed outbound logons made by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrHistoryMapEntries.name: nntpSrvrHistoryMapEntries
nntpSrvrHistoryMapEntries.description: History Map Entries is the entries inserted into the history mapping table of the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrHistoryMapEntriesPerSec.name: nntpSrvrHistoryMapEntriesPerSec
nntpSrvrHistoryMapEntriesPerSec.description: History Map Entries/Sec is the entries inserted per sec into the history mapping table of the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrMaximumAnonymousUsers.name: nntpSrvrMaximumAnonymousUsers
nntpSrvrMaximumAnonymousUsers.description: Maximum Anonymous Users is the maximum number of anonymous users simultaneously connected to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrMaximumConnections.name: nntpSrvrMaximumConnections
nntpSrvrMaximumConnections.description: Maximum Connections is the maximum number of simultaneous connections to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrMaximumNonAnonymousUsers.name: nntpSrvrMaximumNonAnonymousUsers
nntpSrvrMaximumNonAnonymousUsers.description: Maximum NonAnonymous Users is the maximum number of nonanonymous users simultaneously connected to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrModeratedPostingsFailed.name: nntpSrvrModeratedPostingsFailed
nntpSrvrModeratedPostingsFailed.description: Moderated Postings Failed is the total number of moderated postings the NNTP Server fails to send to an SMTP Server.

nntpSrvrModeratedPostingsSent.name: nntpSrvrModeratedPostingsSent
nntpSrvrModeratedPostingsSent.description: Moderated Postings Sent is the total number of moderated postings the NNTP Server attempts to send to an SMTP Server.

nntpSrvrSessionsFlowControlled.name: nntpSrvrSessionsFlowControlled
nntpSrvrSessionsFlowControlled.description: Sessions Flow Control is the number of client sessions currently in a flow controlled state in the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrTotalAnonymousUsers.name: nntpSrvrTotalAnonymousUsers
nntpSrvrTotalAnonymousUsers.description: Total Anonymous Users is the total number of anonymous users that have ever connected to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrTotalConnections.name: nntpSrvrTotalConnections
nntpSrvrTotalConnections.description: Total Connections is the number of connections that have been made to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrTotalNonAnonymousUsers.name: nntpSrvrTotalNonAnonymousUsers
nntpSrvrTotalNonAnonymousUsers.description: Total NonAnonymous Users is the total number of nonanonymous users that have ever connected to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrTotalOutboundConnections.name: nntpSrvrTotalOutboundConnections
nntpSrvrTotalOutboundConnections.description: Total Outbound Connections is the number of outbound connections that have been made by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrTotalOutboundConnsFailed.name: nntpSrvrTotalOutboundConnsFailed
nntpSrvrTotalOutboundConnsFailed.description: Total Outbound Connections Failed is the number of unsucessful outbound connections that have been made by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrTotalPassiveFeeds.name: nntpSrvrTotalPassiveFeeds
nntpSrvrTotalPassiveFeeds.description: Total Passive Feeds is the number of passive feeds accepted by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrTotalPullFeeds.name: nntpSrvrTotalPullFeeds
nntpSrvrTotalPullFeeds.description: Total Pull Feeds is the number of pull feeds made by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrTotalPushFeeds.name: nntpSrvrTotalPushFeeds
nntpSrvrTotalPushFeeds.description: Total Push Feeds is the number of push feeds made by the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrTotalSSLConnections.name: nntpSrvrTotalSSLConnections
nntpSrvrTotalSSLConnections.description: Total SSL Connections is the number of SSL connections that have been made to the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrXoverEntries.name: nntpSrvrXoverEntries
nntpSrvrXoverEntries.description: Xover Entries is the number of xover entries in the xover table table of the NNTP Server.

nntpSrvrXoverEntriesPerSec.name: nntpSrvrXoverEntriesPerSec
nntpSrvrXoverEntriesPerSec.description: Xover Entries/Sec is the number of xover entries inserted per sec in the xover table table of the NNTP Server.

ntdsDRAInboundBytesNotCWSSBoot.description: Number of bytes replicated in that were not compressed at the source (i.e., from DSAs in the same site).

ntdsDRAInboundBytesNotCWSPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundBytesNotCWSPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundBytesNotCWSPerSec.description: Number of bytes replicated in that were not compressed at the source (i.e., from DSAs in the same site).

ntdsDRAInboundBytesTotalBoot.name: ntdsDRAInboundBytesTotalBoot
ntdsDRAInboundBytesTotalBoot.description: Total number of bytes replicated in. Sum of the number of uncompressed bytes (never compressed) and the number of compressed bytes (after compression).

ntdsDRAInboundBytesTotalPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundBytesTotalPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundBytesTotalPerSec.description: Total number of bytes replicated in. Sum of the number of uncompressed bytes (never compressed) and the number of compressed bytes (after compression).

ntdsDRAInboundFullSyncObjsRemain.name: ntdsDRAInboundFullSyncObjsRemain
ntdsDRAInboundFullSyncObjsRemain.description: Number of objects remaining until the full sync completes (when set).

ntdsDRAInboundObjUpdsRemainInPkt.name: ntdsDRAInboundObjUpdsRemainInPkt
ntdsDRAInboundObjUpdsRemainInPkt.description: The number of object updates received in the current directory replication update packet that have not yet been applied to the local server.

ntdsDRAInboundObjsAppliedPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundObjsAppliedPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundObjsAppliedPerSec.description: The rate at which replication updates received from replication partners are applied by the local directory service. This count excludes changes that are received but not applied (e.g., when the change is already present). This indicates how much replication update activity is occuring on the server as a result of changes generated on other servers.

ntdsDRAInboundObjsFilteredPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundObjsFilteredPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundObjsFilteredPerSec.description: Number of objects received from inbound replication partners that contained no updates that needed to be applied.

ntdsDRAInboundObjectsPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundObjectsPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundObjectsPerSec.description: No of objects received from neighbors through inbound replication.

ntdsDRAInboundPropAppliedPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundPropAppliedPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundPropAppliedPerSec.description: No of properties that are updated due to incoming property winning the reconciliation logic.

ntdsDRAInboundPropFilteredPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundPropFilteredPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundPropFilteredPerSec.description: No of property changes that are received during the replication that we have already seen.

ntdsDRAInboundPropTotalPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundPropTotalPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundPropTotalPerSec.description: Total number of object properties received from inbound replication partners.

ntdsDRAInboundValuesDNsPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundValuesDNsPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundValuesDNsPerSec.description: Number of object property values received from inbound replication partners that are Distinguished Names; i.e., that reference other objects. DN-values, such as group or distribution list memberships, are generally more expensive to apply than other kinds of values.

ntdsDRAInboundValuesTotalPerSec.name: ntdsDRAInboundValuesTotalPerSec
ntdsDRAInboundValuesTotalPerSec.description: Total number of object property values received from inbound replication partners. Each inbound object has one or more properties, and each property has zero or more values. Zero values indicates property removal.

ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSACSBoot.name: ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSACSBoot
ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSACSBoot.description: Compressed size in bytes of outbound compressed replication data (size after compression, from DSAs in other sites).

ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSACPerSec.name: ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSACPerSec
ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSACPerSec.description: Compressed size in bytes of outbound compressed replication data (size after compression, from DSAs in other sites).

ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSBCSBoot.name: ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSBCSBoot
ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSBCSBoot.description: Original size in bytes of outbound compressed replication data (size before compression, from DSAs in other sites).

ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSBCPerSec.name: ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSBCPerSec
ntdsDRAOutboundBytesCBSBCPerSec.description: Original size in bytes of outbound compressed replication data (size before compression, from DSAs in other sites).

ntdsDRAOutboundBytesNotCWSSBoot.name: ntdsDRAOutboundBytesNotCWSSBoot
ntdsDRAOutboundBytesNotCWSSBoot.description: Number of bytes replicated out that were not compressed (i.e., from DSAs in the same site).

ntdsDRAOutboundBytesNotCWSPerSec.name: ntdsDRAOutboundBytesNotCWSPerSec
ntdsDRAOutboundBytesNotCWSPerSec.description: Number of bytes replicated out that were not compressed (i.e., from DSAs in the same site).

ntdsDRAOutboundBytesTotalBoot.name: ntdsDRAOutboundBytesTotalBoot
ntdsDRAOutboundBytesTotalBoot.description: Total number of bytes replicated out. Sum of the number of uncompressed bytes (never compressed) and the number of compressed bytes (after compression).

ntdsDRAOutboundBytesTotalPerSec.name: ntdsDRAOutboundBytesTotalPerSec
ntdsDRAOutboundBytesTotalPerSec.description: Total number of bytes replicated out. Sum of the number of uncompressed bytes (never compressed) and the number of compressed bytes (after compression).

ntdsDRAOutboundObjsFilterPerSec.name: ntdsDRAOutboundObjsFilterPerSec
ntdsDRAOutboundObjsFilterPerSec.description: Number of objects looked at by outbound replication that were determined to have no updates that the outbound partner did not already have.

ntdsDRAOutboundValuesDNsPerSec.name: ntdsDRAOutboundValuesDNsPerSec
ntdsDRAOutboundValuesDNsPerSec.description: Number of object property values containing Distinguished Names sent to outbound replication partners. DN-values, such as group or distribution list memberships, are generally more expensive to read than other kinds of values.

ntdsDRAOutboundValuesTotalPerSec.name: ntdsDRAOutboundValuesTotalPerSec
ntdsDRAOutboundValuesTotalPerSec.description: Number of object property values sent to outbound replication partners.

ntdsDRAPendingReplicationSync.name: ntdsDRAPendingReplicationSync
ntdsDRAPendingReplicationSync.description: DRA Pending Replication Synchronizations is the number of directory synchronizations that are queued for this server but not yet processed.

ntdsDRASyncFailOnSchemaMismatch.name: ntdsDRASyncFailOnSchemaMismatch
ntdsDRASyncFailOnSchemaMismatch.description: No of sync requests made to the neighbors that failed because their schema are out of sync.

ntdsDRASyncRequestsMade.name: ntdsDRASyncRequestsMade
ntdsDRASyncRequestsMade.description: No of sync requests made to the neighbors.

ntdsDRASyncRequestsSuccessful.name: ntdsDRASyncRequestsSuccessful
ntdsDRASyncRequestsSuccessful.description: No of sync requests made to the neighbors that successfully returned.

ntdsDSPercentReadsOther.name: ntdsDSPercentReadsOther
ntdsDSPercentReadsOther.description: % of directory reads not coming from SAM/DRA/LDAP/LSA/XDS/KCC/NSPI.

ntdsDSPercentReadsFromDRA.name: ntdsDSPercentReadsFromDRA
ntdsDSPercentReadsFromDRA.description: % of directory reads coming from DRA.

ntdsDSPercentReadsFromKCC.name: ntdsDSPercentReadsFromKCC
ntdsDSPercentReadsFromKCC.description: % of directory reads coming from KCC.

ntdsDSPercentReadsFromLSA.name: ntdsDSPercentReadsFromLSA
ntdsDSPercentReadsFromLSA.description: % of directory reads coming from LSA.

ntdsDSPercentReadsFromNSPI.name: ntdsDSPercentReadsFromNSPI
ntdsDSPercentReadsFromNSPI.description: % of directory reads coming from NSPI.

ntdsDSPercentReadsFromSAM.name: ntdsDSPercentReadsFromSAM
ntdsDSPercentReadsFromSAM.description: % of directory reads coming from SAM.

ntdsDSPercentReadsFromXDS.name: ntdsDSPercentReadsFromXDS
ntdsDSPercentReadsFromXDS.description: % of directory reads coming from XDS.

ntdsDSPercentSearchesOther.name: ntdsDSPercentSearchesOther
ntdsDSPercentSearchesOther.description: % of directory searches not coming from SAM/DRA/LDAP/LSA/XDS/KCC/NSPI.

ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromDRA.name: ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromDRA
ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromDRA.description: % of directory searches coming from DRA.

ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromKCC.name: ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromKCC
ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromKCC.description: % of directory searches coming from KCC.

ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromLDAP.name: ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromLDAP
ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromLDAP.description: % of directory searches coming from LDAP.

ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromLSA.name: ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromLSA
ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromLSA.description: % of directory searches coming from LSA.

ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromNSPI.name: ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromNSPI
ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromNSPI.description: % of directory searches coming from NSPI.

ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromSAM.name: ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromSAM
ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromSAM.description: % of directory searches coming from SAM.

ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromXDS.name: ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromXDS
ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromXDS.description: % of directory searches coming from XDS.

ntdsDSPercentWritesOther.name: ntdsDSPercentWritesOther
ntdsDSPercentWritesOther.description: % of directory writes not coming from SAM/DRA/LDAP/LSA/XDS/KCC/NSPI.

ntdsDSPercentWritesFromDRA.name: ntdsDSPercentWritesFromDRA
ntdsDSPercentWritesFromDRA.description: % of directory writes coming from DRA.

ntdsDSPercentWritesFromKCC.name: ntdsDSPercentWritesFromKCC
ntdsDSPercentWritesFromKCC.description: % of directory writes coming from KCC.

ntdsDSPercentWritesFromLDAP.name: ntdsDSPercentWritesFromLDAP
ntdsDSPercentWritesFromLDAP.description: % of directory writes coming from LDAP.

ntdsDSPercentWritesFromLSA.name: ntdsDSPercentWritesFromLSA
ntdsDSPercentWritesFromLSA.description: % of directory writes coming from LSA.

ntdsDSPercentWritesFromNSPI.name: ntdsDSPercentWritesFromNSPI
ntdsDSPercentWritesFromNSPI.description: % of directory writes coming from NSPI.

ntdsDSPercentWritesFromSAM.name: ntdsDSPercentWritesFromSAM
ntdsDSPercentWritesFromSAM.description: % of directory writes coming from SAM.

ntdsDSPercentWritesFromXDS.name: ntdsDSPercentWritesFromXDS
ntdsDSPercentWritesFromXDS.description: % of directory writes coming from XDS.

ntdsDSClientBindsPerSec.name: ntdsDSClientBindsPerSec
ntdsDSClientBindsPerSec.description: Number of ntdsapi.dll binds per second serviced by this DC.

ntdsDSClientNameTranslatePerSec.name: ntdsDSClientNameTranslatePerSec
ntdsDSClientNameTranslatePerSec.description: Number of ntdsapi.dll name translations per second serviced by this DC.

ntdsDSDirectoryReadsPerSec.name: ntdsDSDirectoryReadsPerSec
ntdsDSDirectoryReadsPerSec.description: Number of directory reads per second.

ntdsDSDirectorySearchesPerSec.name: ntdsDSDirectorySearchesPerSec
ntdsDSDirectorySearchesPerSec.description: Number of directory searches per second.

ntdsDSDirectoryWritesPerSec.name: ntdsDSDirectoryWritesPerSec
ntdsDSDirectoryWritesPerSec.description: Number of directory writes per second.

ntdsDSMonitorListSize.name: ntdsDSMonitorListSize
ntdsDSMonitorListSize.description: The number of requests to be notified when objects are updated that are currently registered with this DSA.

ntdsDSNameCacheHitRate.name: ntdsDSNameCacheHitRate
ntdsDSNameCacheHitRate.description: The percentage of directory object name component look ups that are satisfied out of the DSA's name cache.

ntdsDSNotifyQueueSize.name: ntdsDSNotifyQueueSize
ntdsDSNotifyQueueSize.description: The number of pending update notifications that have been queued, but not yet transmitted to clients.

ntdsDSSearchSuboperationsPerSec.name: ntdsDSSearchSuboperationsPerSec
ntdsDSSearchSuboperationsPerSec.description: Number of search suboperations per second. One search operation is made up of many sub operations. A sub operation roughly corresponds to an object the search causes the DS to consider.

ntdsDSSecurityDescPropEvents.name: ntdsDSSecurityDescPropEvents
ntdsDSSecurityDescPropEvents.description: DS Security Descriptor Propagations Events is the number of Security Descriptor Propagation Events that are queued but not yet processed.

ntdsDSSecurityDescPropAvgExTime.name: ntdsDSSecurityDescPropAvgExTime
ntdsDSSecurityDescPropAvgExTime.description: Average length of time the Security Descriptor propagator spends waiting for exclusive access to Data Base elements during a Security Descriptor Propagation sub-operation.

ntdsDSSecurityDescPropRunQueue.name: ntdsDSSecurityDescPropRunQueue
ntdsDSSecurityDescPropRunQueue.description: Number of objects remaining to examine while processing the current DS Security Descriptor Propagator Event.

ntdsDSSecurityDescSubopPerSec.name: ntdsDSSecurityDescSubopPerSec
ntdsDSSecurityDescSubopPerSec.description: Number of Security Descriptor Propagation suboperations per second. One Security Descriptor Propagation operation is made up of many sub operations. A sub operation roughly corresponds to an object the propagation causes the propagator to examine.

ntdsDSServerBindsPerSec.name: ntdsDSServerBindsPerSec
ntdsDSServerBindsPerSec.description: Number of DC-to-DC binds per second serviced by this DC.

ntdsDSServerNameTranslatePerSec.name: ntdsDSServerNameTranslatePerSec
ntdsDSServerNameTranslatePerSec.description: Number of DC-to-DC name translations per second serviced by this DC.

ntdsDSThreadsInUse.name: ntdsDSThreadsInUse
ntdsDSThreadsInUse.description: DS Threads in Use is the current number of threads in use by the directory service (different than the number of threads in the directory service process). Threads in Use is the number of threads currently servicing client API calls and can be used to indicate whether additional processors could be of benefit.

ntdsKDCASRequests.name: ntdsKDCASRequests
ntdsKDCASRequests.description: The number of AS requests serviced by the KDC per second. AS requests are used by client to obtain a ticket granting ticket.

ntdsKDCTGSRequests.name: ntdsKDCTGSRequests
ntdsKDCTGSRequests.description: The number of TGS requests serviced by the KDC per second. TGS requests are used by the client to obtain a ticket to a resource.

ntdsKerberosAuthentications.name: ntdsKerberosAuthentications
ntdsKerberosAuthentications.description: The number of times per second that clients use a ticket to this DC to authenticate to this DC.

ntdsLDAPActiveThreads.name: ntdsLDAPActiveThreads
ntdsLDAPActiveThreads.description: LDAP Active Threads is the current number of threads in use by the LDAP subsystem of the local direcotry service.

ntdsLDAPBindTime.name: ntdsLDAPBindTime
ntdsLDAPBindTime.description: Time (in milliseconds) taken for last successful LDAP bind.

ntdsLDAPClientSessions.name: ntdsLDAPClientSessions
ntdsLDAPClientSessions.description: LDAP Client Sessions is the number of connected LDAP client sessions.

ntdsLDAPSearchesPerSec.name: ntdsLDAPSearchesPerSec
ntdsLDAPSearchesPerSec.description: LDAP Searches/sec is the rate at which LDAP clients perform search operations.

ntdsLDAPSuccessfulBinds.name: ntdsLDAPSuccessfulBinds
ntdsLDAPSuccessfulBinds.description: % of LDAP bind attempts that were successful.

ntdsLDAPSuccessfulBindsPerSec.name: ntdsLDAPSuccessfulBindsPerSec
ntdsLDAPSuccessfulBindsPerSec.description: Number of LDAP Binds per second.

ntdsLDAPUDPOperationsPerSec.name: ntdsLDAPUDPOperationsPerSec
ntdsLDAPUDPOperationsPerSec.description: The number of UDP operations the LDAP server is processing per second.

ntdsLDAPWritesPerSec.name: ntdsLDAPWritesPerSec
ntdsLDAPWritesPerSec.description: LDAP Writes/sec is the rate at which LDAP clients perform write operations.

ntdsNTLMAuthentications.name: ntdsNTLMAuthentications
ntdsNTLMAuthentications.description: Number of NTLM authentications per second serviced by this DC.

ntdsSAMAccountGroupMemEvalPerSec.name: ntdsSAMAccountGroupMemEvalPerSec
ntdsSAMAccountGroupMemEvalPerSec.description: Number of SAM Account Group Membership Evaluations per second.

ntdsSAMDisplayInfoQueriesPerSec.name: ntdsSAMDisplayInfoQueriesPerSec
ntdsSAMDisplayInfoQueriesPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of queries per second to obtain display information (netquerydisplayinformation).

ntdsSAMEnumerationsPerSec.name: ntdsSAMEnumerationsPerSec
ntdsSAMEnumerationsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of net user, net group, and net local function enumerations per second.

ntdsSAMGCEvaluationsPerSec.name: ntdsSAMGCEvaluationsPerSec
ntdsSAMGCEvaluationsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of universal group membership evaluations per second on a global catalog domain controller from non-global catalog domain controllers.

ntdsSAMMachineCreateAtpsPerSec.name: ntdsSAMMachineCreateAtpsPerSec
ntdsSAMMachineCreateAtpsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of attempts per second to create computer accounts.

ntdsSAMMembershipChangesPerSec.name: ntdsSAMMembershipChangesPerSec
ntdsSAMMembershipChangesPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of group membership changes per second across all global, universal, and nested groups.

ntdsSAMNonTransMemEvalPerSec.name: ntdsSAMNonTransMemEvalPerSec
ntdsSAMNonTransMemEvalPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of net user and new local groups evaluations per second when performing a non-transitive membership evaluation.

ntdsSAMPasswordChangesPerSec.name: ntdsSAMPasswordChangesPerSec
ntdsSAMPasswordChangesPerSec.description: Number of SAM password changes per second.

ntdsSAMResourceGrpMemEvalPerSec.name: ntdsSAMResourceGrpMemEvalPerSec
ntdsSAMResourceGrpMemEvalPerSec.description: Number of SAM Resource Group Membership Evaluations per second.

ntdsSAMSuccessMachineCreatPerSec.name: ntdsSAMSuccessMachineCreatPerSec
ntdsSAMSuccessMachineCreatPerSec.description: Number of successful machine creations per second.

ntdsSAMSuccessUserCreatePerSec.name: ntdsSAMSuccessUserCreatePerSec
ntdsSAMSuccessUserCreatePerSec.description: This counter displays the number of user accounts successfully created per second.

ntdsSAMTransitiveMembEvalPerSec.name: ntdsSAMTransitiveMembEvalPerSec
ntdsSAMTransitiveMembEvalPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of new groups encountered per second when performing a transitive membership evaluation. Evaluations are performed at authentication time and when computer accounts or attributes are created.

ntdsSAMUniversalGrpMemEvalPerSec.name: ntdsSAMUniversalGrpMemEvalPerSec
ntdsSAMUniversalGrpMemEvalPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of universal group membership evaluations per second at authentication time.

ntdsSAMUserCreateAttemptsPerSec.name: ntdsSAMUserCreateAttemptsPerSec
ntdsSAMUserCreateAttemptsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of attempts per second to create user accounts.

ntdsXDSClientSessions.name: ntdsXDSClientSessions
ntdsXDSClientSessions.description: XDS Client Sessions is the number of connected Extended Directory Service client sessions. This indicates the number of connections from other Windows NT services and the Windows NT Administrator program.

ntdsDRAInLnkValUpdsRemainInPckt.name: ntdsDRAInLnkValUpdsRemainInPckt
ntdsDRAInLnkValUpdsRemainInPckt.description: The number of link value updates received in the current directory replication update packet that have not yet been applied to the local server.

ntdsDRAInTotalUpdsRemainInPacket.name: ntdsDRAInTotalUpdsRemainInPacket
ntdsDRAInTotalUpdsRemainInPacket.description: The number of total (link values + object) updates received in the current directory replication update packet that have not yet been applied to the local server.

ntdsDRAPendReplicationOps.name: ntdsDRAPendReplicationOps
ntdsDRAPendReplicationOps.description: The total number of replication operations on the directory that are queued for this server but not yet performed.

ntdsDRAThreadsGettingNCChanges.name: ntdsDRAThreadsGettingNCChanges
ntdsDRAThreadsGettingNCChanges.description: The number of threads on the server which are currently attempting to acquire changes from another server.

ntdsDRAThdsGetNCChngsHoldSmphr.name: ntdsDRAThdsGetNCChngsHoldSmphr
ntdsDRAThdsGetNCChngsHoldSmphr.description: The number of threads on the server which are currently attempting to acquire changes from another server and hold a semaphore required to get these changes.

ntdsDSPercentReadsFromNTDSAPI.name: ntdsDSPercentReadsFromNTDSAPI
ntdsDSPercentReadsFromNTDSAPI.description: % of directory reads coming from NTDAPI calls.

ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromNTDSAPI.name: ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromNTDSAPI
ntdsDSPercentSearchesFromNTDSAPI.description: % of directory searches coming from NTDAPI calls.

ntdsDSPercentWritesFromNTDSAPI.name: ntdsDSPercentWritesFromNTDSAPI
ntdsDSPercentWritesFromNTDSAPI.description: % of directory writes coming from NTDSAPI calls.

ntdsLDAPClosedConnectionsPerSec.name: ntdsLDAPClosedConnectionsPerSec
ntdsLDAPClosedConnectionsPerSec.description: The number of LDAP connections that have been closed in the last second.

ntdsLDAPNewConnectionsPerSec.name: ntdsLDAPNewConnectionsPerSec
ntdsLDAPNewConnectionsPerSec.description: The number of new LDAP connections that have arrived in the last second.

ntdsLDAPNewSSLConnectionsPerSec.name: ntdsLDAPNewSSLConnectionsPerSec
ntdsLDAPNewSSLConnectionsPerSec.description: The number of new SSL or TLS connections that arrived in the last second.

ntdsSAMAccountGroupEvalLatency.name: ntdsSAMAccountGroupEvalLatency
ntdsSAMAccountGroupEvalLatency.description: The mean latency of the last 100 account and universal group evaluations performed for authentication.

ntdsSAMResourceGroupEvalLatency.name: ntdsSAMResourceGroupEvalLatency
ntdsSAMResourceGroupEvalLatency.description: The mean latency of the last 100 resource group evaluations performed for authentication.

ntdsATQEstimatedQueueDelay.name: ntdsATQEstimatedQueueDelay
ntdsATQEstimatedQueueDelay.description: Estimated time (in milliseconds) the next request will spend in the queue prior to being serviced by the directory service.

ntdsATQOutstandingQueuedRequests.name: ntdsATQOutstandingQueuedRequests
ntdsATQOutstandingQueuedRequests.description: The number of requests currently queued and waiting to be serviced.

ntdsATQRequestLatency.name: ntdsATQRequestLatency
ntdsATQRequestLatency.description: Average length of time (in milliseconds) to process a request, not including time spent on the queue.

ntdsLinkValuesCleanedPerSec.name: ntdsLinkValuesCleanedPerSec
ntdsLinkValuesCleanedPerSec.description: The rate at which link values that need to be cleaned are cleaned.

ntdsPhantomsCleanedPerSec.name: ntdsPhantomsCleanedPerSec
ntdsPhantomsCleanedPerSec.description: The rate at which stale phantoms are cleaned.

ntdsPhantomsVisitedPerSec.name: ntdsPhantomsVisitedPerSec
ntdsPhantomsVisitedPerSec.description: The rate at which phantoms are visited to determine if they are stale and need to be cleaned.

ntdsSAMDomLocGrpMembEvalsPerSec.name: ntdsSAMDomLocGrpMembEvalsPerSec
ntdsSAMDomLocGrpMembEvalsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of domain local group memberships evaluations per second at authentication time.

ntdsSAMGlbGrpMembpEvalsPerSec.name: ntdsSAMGlbGrpMembpEvalsPerSec
ntdsSAMGlbGrpMembpEvalsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of domain global group membership evaluations per second at authentication time.

ntdsSAMSuccessCompCreationPerSec.name: ntdsSAMSuccessCompCreationPerSec
ntdsSAMSuccessCompCreationPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of successful computer accounts created per second.

ntdsTombstonesGarbageCollPerSec.name: ntdsTombstonesGarbageCollPerSec
ntdsTombstonesGarbageCollPerSec.description: The rate at which expired tombstoned objects are garbage collected.

ntdsTombstonesVisitedPerSec.name: ntdsTombstonesVisitedPerSec
ntdsTombstonesVisitedPerSec.description: The rate at which tombstoned objects are visited to be considered for garbage collected.

nwLinkIPXTable.name: nwLinkIPXTable
nwLinkIPXTable.description: The NWLink IPX performance object consists of counters that measure datagram transmission to and from computers using the IPX protocol. This object only reports valid data for counters that monitor datagrams and packets; for frame-related counters, the object tends to report zero values. In addition, connection-related data is not likely to be useful because IPX is a connectionless protocol.

nwLinkIPXEntry.name: nwLinkIPXEntry
nwLinkIPXEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'NWLink IPX' object.

ipxBytesTotalPerSec.name: ipxBytesTotalPerSec
ipxBytesTotalPerSec.description: Bytes Total/sec is the sum of Frame Bytes/sec and Datagram Bytes/sec. This is the total rate of bytes sent to or received from the network by the protocol, but only counts the bytes in frames (i.e., packets) which carry data.

ipxConnectionSessionTimeouts.name: ipxConnectionSessionTimeouts
ipxConnectionSessionTimeouts.description: Connection Session Timeouts is the number of connections that were dropped due to a session timeout. This number is an accumulator and shows a running total.

ipxConnectionsCanceled.name: ipxConnectionsCanceled
ipxConnectionsCanceled.description: Connections Canceled is the number of connections that were canceled. This number is an accumulator and shows a running total.

ipxConnectionsNoRetries.name: ipxConnectionsNoRetries
ipxConnectionsNoRetries.description: Connections No Retries is the total count of connections that were successfully made on the first try. This number is an accumulator and shows a running total.

ipxConnectionsOpen.name: ipxConnectionsOpen
ipxConnectionsOpen.description: Connections Open is the number of connections currently open for this protocol. This counter shows the current count only and does not accumulate over time.

ipxConnectionsWithRetries.name: ipxConnectionsWithRetries
ipxConnectionsWithRetries.description: Connections With Retries is the total count of connections that were made after retrying the attempt. A retry occurs when the first connection attempt failed. This number is an accumulator and shows a running total.

ipxDatagramBytesReceivedPerSec.name: ipxDatagramBytesReceivedPerSec
ipxDatagramBytesReceivedPerSec.description: Datagram Bytes Received/sec is the rate at which datagram bytes are received by the computer. A datagram is a connectionless packet whose delivery to a remote computer is not guaranteed.

ipxDatagramBytesSentPerSec.name: ipxDatagramBytesSentPerSec
ipxDatagramBytesSentPerSec.description: Datagram Bytes Sent/sec is the rate at which datagram bytes are sent from the computer. A datagram is a connectionless packet whose delivery to a remote computer is not guaranteed.

ipxDatagramBytesPerSec.name: ipxDatagramBytesPerSec
ipxDatagramBytesPerSec.description: Datagram Bytes/sec is the rate at which datagram bytes are processed by the computer. This counter is the sum of datagram bytes that are sent as well as received. A datagram is a connectionless packet whose delivery to a remote is not guaranteed.

ipxDatagramsReceivedPerSec.name: ipxDatagramsReceivedPerSec
ipxDatagramsReceivedPerSec.description: Datagrams Received/sec is the rate at which datagrams are received by the computer. A datagram is a connectionless packet whose delivery to a remote computer is not guaranteed.

ipxDatagramsSentPerSec.name: ipxDatagramsSentPerSec
ipxDatagramsSentPerSec.description: Datagrams Sent/sec is the rate at which datagrams are sent from the computer. A datagram is a connectionless packet whose delivery to a remote computer is not guaranteed.

ipxDatagramsPerSec.name: ipxDatagramsPerSec
ipxDatagramsPerSec.description: Datagrams/sec is the rate at which datagrams are processed by the computer. This counter displays the sum of datagrams sent and datagrams received. A datagram is a connectionless packet whose delivery to a remote is not guaranteed.

ipxDisconnectsLocal.name: ipxDisconnectsLocal
ipxDisconnectsLocal.description: Disconnects Local is the number of session disconnections that were initiated by the local computer. This number is an accumulator and shows a running total.

ipxDisconnectsRemote.name: ipxDisconnectsRemote
ipxDisconnectsRemote.description: Disconnects Remote is the number of session disconnections that were initiated by the remote computer. This number is an accumulator and shows a running total.

ipxExpirationsAck.name: ipxExpirationsAck
ipxExpirationsAck.description: Expirations Ack is the count of T2 timer expirations.

ipxExpirationsResponse.name: ipxExpirationsResponse
ipxExpirationsResponse.description: Expirations Response is the count of T1 timer expirations.

ipxFailuresAdapter.name: ipxFailuresAdapter
ipxFailuresAdapter.description: Failures Adapter is the number of connections that were dropped due to an adapter failure. This number is an accumulator and shows a running total.

ipxFailuresLink.name: ipxFailuresLink

ipxFramesReSentPerSec.name: ipxFramesReSentPerSec
ipxFramesReSentPerSec.description: Frames Re-Sent/sec is the rate at which data frames (packets) are re-sent by the computer. This counter only counts the frames or packets that carry data.

ipxFramesReceivedPerSec.name: ipxFramesReceivedPerSec
ipxFramesReceivedPerSec.description: Frames Received/sec is the rate at which data frames are received by the computer. This counter only counts the frames (packets) that carry data.

ipxFramesRejectedPerSec.name: ipxFramesRejectedPerSec
ipxFramesRejectedPerSec.description: Frames Rejected/sec is the rate at which data frames are rejected. This counter only counts the frames (packets) that carry data.

ipxFramesSentPerSec.name: ipxFramesSentPerSec
ipxFramesSentPerSec.description: Frames Sent/sec is the rate at which data frames are sent by the computer. This counter only counts the frames (packets) that carry data.

ipxFramesPerSec.name: ipxFramesPerSec
ipxFramesPerSec.description: Frames/sec is the rate at which data frames (or packets) are processed by the computer. This counter is the sum of data frames sent and data frames received. This counter only counts those frames (packets) that carry data.

ipxPacketsReceivedPerSec.name: ipxPacketsReceivedPerSec
ipxPacketsReceivedPerSec.description: Packets Received/sec is the rate at which packets are received by the computer. This counter counts all packets processed: control as well as data packets.

ipxPacketsSentPerSec.name: ipxPacketsSentPerSec
ipxPacketsSentPerSec.description: Packets Sent/sec is the rate at which packets are sent by the computer. This counter counts all packets sent by the computer, i.e. control as well as data packets.

ipxPacketsPerSec.name: ipxPacketsPerSec
ipxPacketsPerSec.description: Packets/sec is the rate at which packets are processed by the computer. This count is the sum of Packets Sent and Packets Received per second. This counter includes all packets processed: control as well as data packets.

ipxPiggybackAckQueuedPerSec.name: ipxPiggybackAckQueuedPerSec
ipxPiggybackAckQueuedPerSec.description: Piggyback Ack Queued/sec is the rate at which piggybacked acknowledgments are queued. Piggyback acknowledgments are acknowledgments to received packets that are to be included in the next outgoing packet to the remote computer.

ipxPiggybackAckTimeouts.name: ipxPiggybackAckTimeouts
ipxPiggybackAckTimeouts.description: Piggyback Ack Timeouts is the number of times that a piggyback acknowledgment could not be sent because there was no outgoing packet to the remote on which to piggyback. A piggyback ack is an acknowledgment to a received packet that is sent along in an outgoing data packet to the remote computer. If no outgoing packet is sent within the timeout period, then an ack packet is sent and this counter is incremented.

ipxWindowSendAverage.name: ipxWindowSendAverage
ipxWindowSendAverage.description: Window Send Average is the running average number of data bytes that were sent before waiting for an acknowledgment from the remote computer.

ipxWindowSendMaximum.name: ipxWindowSendMaximum
ipxWindowSendMaximum.description: Window Send Maximum is the maximum number of bytes of data that will be sent before waiting for an acknowledgment from the remote computer.

nwLinkNetBIOSTable.name: nwLinkNetBIOSTable
nwLinkNetBIOSTable.description: The NWLink NetBIOS performance object consists of counters that monitor IPX transport rates and connections. This object only reports valid data for counters that monitor datagrams and packets; for frame-related counters, the object tends to report zero values.

nwLinkNetBIOSEntry.name: nwLinkNetBIOSEntry
nwLinkNetBIOSEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'NWLink NetBIOS' object.

netBIOSBytesTotalPerSec.name: netBIOSBytesTotalPerSec
netBIOSBytesTotalPerSec.description: Bytes Total/sec is the sum of Frame Bytes/sec and Datagram Bytes/sec. This is the total rate of bytes sent to or received from the network by the protocol, but only counts the bytes in frames (i.e., packets) which carry data.

netBIOSConnectionSessionTimeouts.name: netBIOSConnectionSessionTimeouts
netBIOSConnectionSessionTimeouts.description: Connection Session Timeouts is the number of connections that were dropped due to a session timeout. This number is an accumulator and shows a running total.

netBIOSConnectionsCanceled.name: netBIOSConnectionsCanceled

netBIOSConnectionsNoRetries.name: netBIOSConnectionsNoRetries

netBIOSConnectionsOpen.name: netBIOSConnectionsOpen
netBIOSConnectionsOpen.description: Connections Open is the number of connections currently open for this protocol. This counter shows the current count only and does not accumulate over time.

netBIOSConnectionsWithRetries.name: netBIOSConnectionsWithRetries

netBIOSDatagramBytesRcvdPerSec.name: netBIOSDatagramBytesRcvdPerSec
netBIOSDatagramBytesRcvdPerSec.description: Datagram Bytes Received/sec is the rate at which datagram bytes are received by the computer. A datagram is a connectionless packet whose delivery to a remote computer is not guaranteed.

netBIOSDatagramBytesSentPerSec.name: netBIOSDatagramBytesSentPerSec
netBIOSDatagramBytesSentPerSec.description: Datagram Bytes Sent/sec is the rate at which datagram bytes are sent from the computer. A datagram is a connectionless packet whose delivery to a remote computer is not guaranteed.

netBIOSDatagramsReceivedPerSec.name: netBIOSDatagramsReceivedPerSec
netBIOSDatagramsReceivedPerSec.description: Datagrams Received/sec is the rate at which datagrams are received by the computer. A datagram is a connectionless packet whose delivery to a remote computer is not guaranteed.

netBIOSDisconnectsRemote.description: Disconnects Remote is the number of session disconnections that were initiated by the remote computer. This number is an accumulator and shows a running total.
