dsDSPercentReadsFromLSA.description: % of directory reads coming from LSA.

dsDSPercentReadsFromNSPI.name: dsDSPercentReadsFromNSPI
dsDSPercentReadsFromNSPI.description: % of directory reads coming from NSPI.

dsDSPercentReadsFromNTDSAPI.name: dsDSPercentReadsFromNTDSAPI
dsDSPercentReadsFromNTDSAPI.description: % of directory reads coming from NTDAPI calls.

dsDSPercentReadsFromSAM.name: dsDSPercentReadsFromSAM
dsDSPercentReadsFromSAM.description: % of directory reads coming from SAM.

dsDSPercentSearchesOther.name: dsDSPercentSearchesOther
dsDSPercentSearchesOther.description: % of directory searches not coming from SAM/DRA/LDAP/LSA/XDS/KCC/NSPI.

dsDSPercentSearchesFromDRA.name: dsDSPercentSearchesFromDRA
dsDSPercentSearchesFromDRA.description: % of directory searches coming from DRA.

dsDSPercentSearchesFromKCC.name: dsDSPercentSearchesFromKCC
dsDSPercentSearchesFromKCC.description: % of directory searches coming from KCC.

dsDSPercentSearchesFromLDAP.name: dsDSPercentSearchesFromLDAP
dsDSPercentSearchesFromLDAP.description: % of directory searches coming from LDAP.

dsDSPercentSearchesFromLSA.name: dsDSPercentSearchesFromLSA
dsDSPercentSearchesFromLSA.description: % of directory searches coming from LSA.

dsDSPercentSearchesFromNSPI.name: dsDSPercentSearchesFromNSPI
dsDSPercentSearchesFromNSPI.description: % of directory searches coming from NSPI.

dsDSPercentSearchesFromNTDSAPI.name: dsDSPercentSearchesFromNTDSAPI
dsDSPercentSearchesFromNTDSAPI.description: % of directory searches coming from NTDAPI calls.

dsDSPercentSearchesFromSAM.name: dsDSPercentSearchesFromSAM
dsDSPercentSearchesFromSAM.description: % of directory searches coming from SAM.

dsDSPercentWritesOther.name: dsDSPercentWritesOther
dsDSPercentWritesOther.description: % of directory writes not coming from SAM/DRA/LDAP/LSA/XDS/KCC/NSPI.

dsDSPercentWritesFromDRA.name: dsDSPercentWritesFromDRA
dsDSPercentWritesFromDRA.description: % of directory writes coming from DRA.

dsDSPercentWritesFromKCC.name: dsDSPercentWritesFromKCC
dsDSPercentWritesFromKCC.description: % of directory writes coming from KCC.

dsDSPercentWritesFromLDAP.name: dsDSPercentWritesFromLDAP
dsDSPercentWritesFromLDAP.description: % of directory writes coming from LDAP.

dsDSPercentWritesFromLSA.name: dsDSPercentWritesFromLSA
dsDSPercentWritesFromLSA.description: % of directory writes coming from LSA.

dsDSPercentWritesFromNSPI.name: dsDSPercentWritesFromNSPI
dsDSPercentWritesFromNSPI.description: % of directory writes coming from NSPI.

dsDSPercentWritesFromNTDSAPI.name: dsDSPercentWritesFromNTDSAPI
dsDSPercentWritesFromNTDSAPI.description: % of directory writes coming from NTDSAPI calls.

dsDSPercentWritesFromSAM.name: dsDSPercentWritesFromSAM
dsDSPercentWritesFromSAM.description: % of directory writes coming from SAM.

dsDSClientBindsPerSec.name: dsDSClientBindsPerSec
dsDSClientBindsPerSec.description: Number of ntdsapi.dll binds per second serviced by this DC.

dsDSClientNameTranslationsPerSec.name: dsDSClientNameTranslationsPerSec
dsDSClientNameTranslationsPerSec.description: Number of ntdsapi.dll name translations per second serviced by this DC.

dsDSDirectoryReadsPerSec.name: dsDSDirectoryReadsPerSec
dsDSDirectoryReadsPerSec.description: Number of directory reads per second.

dsDSDirectorySearchesPerSec.name: dsDSDirectorySearchesPerSec
dsDSDirectorySearchesPerSec.description: Number of directory searches per second.

dsDSDirectoryWritesPerSec.name: dsDSDirectoryWritesPerSec
dsDSDirectoryWritesPerSec.description: Number of directory writes per second.

dsDSMonitorListSize.name: dsDSMonitorListSize
dsDSMonitorListSize.description: The number of requests to be notified when objects are updated that are currently registered with this DSA.

dsDSNameCacheHitRate.name: dsDSNameCacheHitRate
dsDSNameCacheHitRate.description: The percentage of directory object name component look ups that are satisfied out of the DSA's name cache.

dsDSNotifyQueueSize.name: dsDSNotifyQueueSize
dsDSNotifyQueueSize.description: The number of pending update notifications that have been queued, but not yet transmitted to clients.

dsDSSearchSubOperationsPerSec.name: dsDSSearchSubOperationsPerSec
dsDSSearchSubOperationsPerSec.description: Number of search suboperations per second. One search operation is made up of many sub operations. A sub operation roughly corresponds to an object the search causes the DS to consider.

dsDSSecurityDescriptorPropEvents.name: dsDSSecurityDescriptorPropEvents
dsDSSecurityDescriptorPropEvents.description: DS Security Descriptor Propagations Events is the number of Security Descriptor Propagation Events that are queued but not yet processed.

dsDSSecurityDescPropAvgExclTime.name: dsDSSecurityDescPropAvgExclTime
dsDSSecurityDescPropAvgExclTime.description: Average length of time the Security Descriptor propagator spends waiting for exclusive access to Data Base elements during a Security Descriptor Propagation sub-operation.

dsDSSecurityDescPropRuntimeQueue.name: dsDSSecurityDescPropRuntimeQueue
dsDSSecurityDescPropRuntimeQueue.description: Number of objects remaining to examine while processing the current DS Security Descriptor Propagator Event.

dsDSSecurityDescSubOpsPerSec.name: dsDSSecurityDescSubOpsPerSec
dsDSSecurityDescSubOpsPerSec.description: Number of Security Descriptor Propagation suboperations per second. One Security Descriptor Propagation operation is made up of many sub operations. A sub operation roughly corresponds to an object the propagation causes the propagator to examine.

dsDSServerBindsPerSec.name: dsDSServerBindsPerSec
dsDSServerBindsPerSec.description: Number of DC-to-DC binds per second serviced by this DC.

dsDSServerNameTranslationsPerSec.name: dsDSServerNameTranslationsPerSec
dsDSServerNameTranslationsPerSec.description: Number of DC-to-DC name translations per second serviced by this DC.

dsDSThreadsInUse.name: dsDSThreadsInUse
dsDSThreadsInUse.description: DS Threads in Use is the current number of threads in use by the directory service (different than the number of threads in the directory service process). Threads in Use is the number of threads currently servicing client API calls and can be used to indicate whether additional processors could be of benefit.

dsLDAPActiveThreads.name: dsLDAPActiveThreads
dsLDAPActiveThreads.description: LDAP Active Threads is the current number of threads in use by the LDAP subsystem of the local direcotry service.

dsLDAPBindTime.name: dsLDAPBindTime
dsLDAPBindTime.description: Time (in milliseconds) taken for last successful LDAP bind.

dsLDAPClientSessions.name: dsLDAPClientSessions
dsLDAPClientSessions.description: LDAP Client Sessions is the number of connected LDAP client sessions.

dsLDAPClosedConnectionsPerSec.name: dsLDAPClosedConnectionsPerSec
dsLDAPClosedConnectionsPerSec.description: The number of LDAP connections that have been closed in the last second.

dsLDAPNewConnectionsPerSec.name: dsLDAPNewConnectionsPerSec
dsLDAPNewConnectionsPerSec.description: The number of new LDAP connections that have arrived in the last second.

dsLDAPNewSSLConnectionsPerSec.name: dsLDAPNewSSLConnectionsPerSec
dsLDAPNewSSLConnectionsPerSec.description: The number of new SSL or TLS connections that arrived in the last second.

dsLDAPSearchesPerSec.name: dsLDAPSearchesPerSec
dsLDAPSearchesPerSec.description: LDAP Searches/sec is the rate at which LDAP clients perform search operations.

dsLDAPSuccessfulBindsPerSec.name: dsLDAPSuccessfulBindsPerSec
dsLDAPSuccessfulBindsPerSec.description: Number of LDAP Binds per second.

dsLDAPUDPOperationsPerSec.name: dsLDAPUDPOperationsPerSec
dsLDAPUDPOperationsPerSec.description: The number of UDP operations the LDAP server is processing per second.

dsLDAPWritesPerSec.name: dsLDAPWritesPerSec
dsLDAPWritesPerSec.description: LDAP Writes/sec is the rate at which LDAP clients perform write operations.

dsLinkValuesCleanedPerSec.name: dsLinkValuesCleanedPerSec
dsLinkValuesCleanedPerSec.description: The rate at which link values that need to be cleaned are cleaned.

dsPhantomsCleanedPerSec.name: dsPhantomsCleanedPerSec
dsPhantomsCleanedPerSec.description: The rate at which stale phantoms are cleaned.

dsPhantomsVisitedPerSec.name: dsPhantomsVisitedPerSec
dsPhantomsVisitedPerSec.description: The rate at which phantoms are visited to determine if they are stale and need to be cleaned.

dsSAMAccountGroupEvalLatency.name: dsSAMAccountGroupEvalLatency
dsSAMAccountGroupEvalLatency.description: The mean latency of the last 100 account and universal group evaluations performed for authentication.

dsSAMDisplayInfoQueriesPerSec.name: dsSAMDisplayInfoQueriesPerSec
dsSAMDisplayInfoQueriesPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of queries per second to obtain display information (netquerydisplayinformation).

dsSAMDomainLocalGrpMemEvalPerSec.name: dsSAMDomainLocalGrpMemEvalPerSec
dsSAMDomainLocalGrpMemEvalPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of domain local group memberships evaluations per second at authentication time.

dsSAMEnumerationsPerSec.name: dsSAMEnumerationsPerSec
dsSAMEnumerationsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of net user, net group, and net local function enumerations per second.

dsSAMGCEvaluationsPerSec.name: dsSAMGCEvaluationsPerSec
dsSAMGCEvaluationsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of universal group membership evaluations per second on a global catalog domain controller from non-global catalog domain controllers.

dsSAMGlobalGroupMembEvalPerSec.name: dsSAMGlobalGroupMembEvalPerSec
dsSAMGlobalGroupMembEvalPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of domain global group membership evaluations per second at authentication time.

dsSAMMachineCreationAttpsPerSec.name: dsSAMMachineCreationAttpsPerSec
dsSAMMachineCreationAttpsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of attempts per second to create computer accounts.

dsSAMMembershipChangesPerSec.name: dsSAMMembershipChangesPerSec
dsSAMMembershipChangesPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of group membership changes per second across all global, universal, and nested groups.

dsSAMNonTransitiveMembEvalPerSec.name: dsSAMNonTransitiveMembEvalPerSec
dsSAMNonTransitiveMembEvalPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of net user and new local groups evaluations per second when performing a non-transitive membership evaluation.

dsSAMPasswordChangesPerSec.name: dsSAMPasswordChangesPerSec
dsSAMPasswordChangesPerSec.description: Number of SAM password changes per second.

dsSAMResourceGroupEvalLatency.name: dsSAMResourceGroupEvalLatency
dsSAMResourceGroupEvalLatency.description: The mean latency of the last 100 resource group evaluations performed for authentication.

dsSAMSuccCmpCrtPerSecInclAllRqst.name: dsSAMSuccCmpCrtPerSecInclAllRqst
dsSAMSuccCmpCrtPerSecInclAllRqst.description: This counter displays the number of successful computer accounts created per second.

dsSAMSuccessUserCreationsPerSec.name: dsSAMSuccessUserCreationsPerSec
dsSAMSuccessUserCreationsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of user accounts successfully created per second.

dsSAMTransitiveMemberEvalPerSec.name: dsSAMTransitiveMemberEvalPerSec
dsSAMTransitiveMemberEvalPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of new groups encountered per second when performing a transitive membership evaluation. Evaluations are performed at authentication time and when computer accounts or attributes are created.

dsSAMUniversalGrpMembEvalPerSec.name: dsSAMUniversalGrpMembEvalPerSec
dsSAMUniversalGrpMembEvalPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of universal group membership evaluations per second at authentication time.

dsSAMUserCreationAttemptsPerSec.name: dsSAMUserCreationAttemptsPerSec
dsSAMUserCreationAttemptsPerSec.description: This counter displays the number of attempts per second to create user accounts.

dsTombstonesGarbageCollPerSec.name: dsTombstonesGarbageCollPerSec
dsTombstonesGarbageCollPerSec.description: The rate at which expired tombstoned objects are garbage collected.

dsTombstonesVisitedPerSec.name: dsTombstonesVisitedPerSec
dsTombstonesVisitedPerSec.description: The rate at which tombstoned objects are visited to be considered for garbage collected.

dfsReplicatedFoldersTable.name: dfsReplicatedFoldersTable
dfsReplicatedFoldersTable.description: The DFS replicated folders performance object. This object includes counters for staging and conflict quotas.

dfsReplicatedFoldersEntry.name: dfsReplicatedFoldersEntry
dfsReplicatedFoldersEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'DFS Replicated Folders' object.

dfsrfBandwidthSavings.name: dfsrfBandwidthSavings
dfsrfBandwidthSavings.description: Bandwidth Savings Using DFS Replication shows the percentage of bandwidth that was saved by the DFS Replication service for this replicated folder using a combination of remote differential compression (RDC) and other compression technologies that minimize network bandwidth. For example, a value of 20 indicates that the DFS Replication service used 20% less bandwidth than it would have used if it had transmitted the entire files uncompressed over the network.

dfsrfCompressedSizeOfFilesRcvd.name: dfsrfCompressedSizeOfFilesRcvd
dfsrfCompressedSizeOfFilesRcvd.description: Compressed Size of Files Received shows the compressed size (in bytes) of files received for this replicated folder.

dfsrfConflictBytesCleanedUp.name: dfsrfConflictBytesCleanedUp
dfsrfConflictBytesCleanedUp.description: Conflict Bytes Cleaned up shows the total size (in bytes) of the conflict loser files and folders that were deleted from the Conflict and Deleted folder by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service automatically detects and resolves conflicts encountered in replicated folders and moves the losing version to the Conflict and Deleted folder. The service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfConflictBytesGenerated.name: dfsrfConflictBytesGenerated
dfsrfConflictBytesGenerated.description: Conflict Bytes Generated shows the total size (in bytes) of the files and folders in this replicated folder that were moved to the Conflict and Deleted folder by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service automatically detects and resolves conflicts encountered in replicated folders and moves the losing version to the Conflict and Deleted folder. The service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfConflictFilesCleanedUp.name: dfsrfConflictFilesCleanedUp
dfsrfConflictFilesCleanedUp.description: Conflict Files Cleaned up shows the number the conflict loser files and folders that were deleted from the Conflict and Deleted folder by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service automatically detects and resolves conflicts encountered in replicated folders and moves the losing version to the Conflict and Deleted folder. The service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfConflictFilesGenerated.name: dfsrfConflictFilesGenerated
dfsrfConflictFilesGenerated.description: Conflict Files Generated shows the number of files and folders in this replicated folder that were moved to the Conflict and Deleted folder by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service automatically detects and resolves conflicts encountered in replicated folders and moves the losing version to the Conflict and Deleted folder. The service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfConflictFolderCleanupsComp.name: dfsrfConflictFolderCleanupsComp
dfsrfConflictFolderCleanupsComp.description: Conflict Folder Cleanups Completed shows the number of times conflict loser files and folders in the Conflict and Deleted folder were deleted by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service automatically detects and resolves conflicts encountered in replicated folders and moves the losing version to the Conflict and Deleted folder. The service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfConflictSpaceInUse.name: dfsrfConflictSpaceInUse
dfsrfConflictSpaceInUse.description: Conflict Space in Use shows the total size (in bytes) of the conflict loser files and folders currently in the Conflict and Deleted folder used by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service automatically detects and resolves conflicts encountered in replicated folders and moves the losing version to the Conflict and Deleted folder. The service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfDeletedBytesCleanedUp.name: dfsrfDeletedBytesCleanedUp
dfsrfDeletedBytesCleanedUp.description: Deleted Bytes Cleaned up shows the total size (in bytes) of replicating deleted files and folders (in bytes) that were cleaned up from the Conflict and Deleted folder by the DFS Replication service. The service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfDeletedBytesGenerated.name: dfsrfDeletedBytesGenerated
dfsrfDeletedBytesGenerated.description: Deleted Bytes Generated shows the total size (in bytes) of replicated deleted files and folders that were moved to the Conflict and Deleted folder after they were deleted from a replicated folder on a sending member. The DFS Replication service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfDeletedFilesCleanedUp.name: dfsrfDeletedFilesCleanedUp
dfsrfDeletedFilesCleanedUp.description: Deleted Files Cleaned up shows the number of replicated deleted files and folders that were cleaned up from the Conflict and Deleted folder by the DFS Replication service. The service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfDeletedFilesGenerated.name: dfsrfDeletedFilesGenerated
dfsrfDeletedFilesGenerated.description: Deleted Files Generated shows the number of replicated deleted files and folders that were moved to the Conflict and Deleted folder after they were deleted from a replicated folder on a sending member. The DFS Replication service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfDeletedSpaceInUse.name: dfsrfDeletedSpaceInUse
dfsrfDeletedSpaceInUse.description: Deleted Space in Use shows the total size (in bytes) of the deleted files and folders currently in the Conflict and Deleted folder used by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service detects remote deletes from its sending partner and moves the file or folder to the Conflict and Deleted folder. The service automatically cleans up the Conflict and Deleted folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfFileInstallsRetried.name: dfsrfFileInstallsRetried
dfsrfFileInstallsRetried.description: File Installs Retried shows the number of file installs that are being retried due to sharing violations or other errors encountered when installing the files. The DFS Replication service replicates staged files into the staging folder, uncompresses them in the Installing folder, and renames them to the target location. The second and third steps of this process are known as installing the file.

dfsrfFileInstallsSucceeded.name: dfsrfFileInstallsSucceeded
dfsrfFileInstallsSucceeded.description: File Installs Succeeded shows the number of files that were successfully received from sending members and installed locally on this server. The DFS Replication service replicates staged files into the staging folder, uncompresses them in the Installing folder, and renames them to the target location. The second and third steps of this process are known as installing the file.

dfsrfRDCBytesReceived.name: dfsrfRDCBytesReceived
dfsrfRDCBytesReceived.description: RDC Bytes Received shows the number of bytes that were received in replicating files using remote differential compression (RDC) for this replicated folder. This is the actual bytes received over the network without the networking protocol overhead.

dfsrfRDCCompressSizeOfFilesRcvd.name: dfsrfRDCCompressSizeOfFilesRcvd
dfsrfRDCCompressSizeOfFilesRcvd.description: RDC Compressed Size of Files Received shows the compressed size (in bytes) of the files received with remote differential compression (RDC) for this replicated folder. This is the number of bytes that would have been received had RDC not been used. This is not the actual bytes received over the network.

dfsrfRDCNumberOfFilesReceived.name: dfsrfRDCNumberOfFilesReceived
dfsrfRDCNumberOfFilesReceived.description: RDC Number of Files Received shows the number files that were received for this replicated folder.

dfsrfRDCSizeOfFilesReceived.name: dfsrfRDCSizeOfFilesReceived
dfsrfRDCSizeOfFilesReceived.description: RDC Size of Files Received shows the uncompressed size (in bytes) of the files received with remote differential compression (RDC) for this replicated folder. This is the number of bytes that would have been received had neither compression nor RDC been used. This is not the actual bytes received over the network.

dfsrfSizeOfFilesReceived.name: dfsrfSizeOfFilesReceived
dfsrfSizeOfFilesReceived.description: Size of Files Received shows the uncompressed size (in bytes) of the files received for this replicated folder. This is the number of bytes that would have been received had DFS Replication compression not been used.

dfsrfStagingBytesCleanedUp.name: dfsrfStagingBytesCleanedUp
dfsrfStagingBytesCleanedUp.description: Staging Bytes Cleaned up shows the total size (in bytes) of the files and folders that were cleaned up from the staging folder by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service stages files and folders in the staging folder before they are replicated, and automatically cleans up the staging folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfStagingBytesGenerated.name: dfsrfStagingBytesGenerated
dfsrfStagingBytesGenerated.description: Staging Bytes Generated shows the total size (in bytes) of replicated files and folders in the staging folder created by the DFS Replication service since last restart and is monotonically increasing counter. The DFS Replication service stages files and folders in the staging folder before they are replicated, and automatically cleans up the staging folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfStagingFilesCleanedUp.name: dfsrfStagingFilesCleanedUp
dfsrfStagingFilesCleanedUp.description: Staging Files Cleaned up shows the number of files and folders that were cleaned up from the staging folder by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service stages files and folders in the staging folder before they are replicated, and automatically cleans up the staging folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfStagingFilesGenerated.name: dfsrfStagingFilesGenerated
dfsrfStagingFilesGenerated.description: Staging Files Generated shows the number of times replicated files and folders were staged by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service stages files and folders in a staging folder before they are replicated, and automatically cleans up the staging folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfStagingSpaceInUse.name: dfsrfStagingSpaceInUse
dfsrfStagingSpaceInUse.description: Staging Files Generated shows the number of times replicated files and folders were staged by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service stages files and folders in a staging folder before they are replicated, and automatically cleans up the staging folder when it exceeds a pre-configured threshold of the quota.

dfsrfTotalFilesReceived.name: dfsrfTotalFilesReceived
dfsrfTotalFilesReceived.description: Total Files Received shows the number of files that were received by this replicated folder.

dfsrfUpdatesDropped.name: dfsrfUpdatesDropped
dfsrfUpdatesDropped.description: Updates Dropped shows the number of redundant file replication update records that were ignored by the DFS Replication service because they did not change the replicated file or folder. For example, dropped updates can occur when access control lists (ACLs) are overwritten with identical ACLs on a file or folder.

dfsReplicationConnectionsTable.name: dfsReplicationConnectionsTable
dfsReplicationConnectionsTable.description: The DFS Replication connections performance object for incoming connections.

dfsReplicationConnectionsEntry.name: dfsReplicationConnectionsEntry
dfsReplicationConnectionsEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'DFS Replication Connections' object.

dfsrcBandwidthSavings.name: dfsrcBandwidthSavings
dfsrcBandwidthSavings.description: Bandwidth Savings Using DFS Replication shows the percentage of bandwidth that was saved by the DFS Replication service for this connection using a combination of remote differential compression (RDC) and other compression technologies that minimize network bandwidth use. For example, a value of 20 indicates that the DFS Replication service used 20% less bandwidth than it would have used if it had transmitted the entire files uncompressed over the network.

dfsrcBytesReceivedPerSecond.name: dfsrcBytesReceivedPerSecond
dfsrcBytesReceivedPerSecond.description: Bytes Received Per Second shows an estimate of the average number of bytes that were received each second over the past 30 seconds.

dfsrcCompressedSizeOfFilesRcvd.name: dfsrcCompressedSizeOfFilesRcvd
dfsrcCompressedSizeOfFilesRcvd.description: Compressed Size of Files Received shows the compressed size of files (in bytes) received on the connection.

dfsrcRDCBytesReceived.name: dfsrcRDCBytesReceived
dfsrcRDCBytesReceived.description: RDC Bytes Received shows the bytes that were received on this connection while replicating files using remote differential compression (RDC). This is the actual bytes received over the network without the networking protocol overhead.

dfsrcRDCCompressSizeOfFilesRcvd.name: dfsrcRDCCompressSizeOfFilesRcvd
dfsrcRDCCompressSizeOfFilesRcvd.description: RDC Compressed Size of Files Received shows the compressed size (in bytes) of files received with remote differential compression (RDC) for this connection. This is the number of bytes that would have been received had RDC not been used. This is not the actual number of bytes received over the network.

dfsrcRDCNumberOfFilesReceived.name: dfsrcRDCNumberOfFilesReceived
dfsrcRDCNumberOfFilesReceived.description: RDC Number of Files Received shows the number files that were received on this connection.

dfsrcRDCSizeOfFilesReceived.name: dfsrcRDCSizeOfFilesReceived
dfsrcRDCSizeOfFilesReceived.description: RDC Size of Files Received shows the uncompressed size (in bytes) of files received with remote differential compression (RDC) for this connection. This is the number of bytes that would have been received had neither compression nor RDC been used. This is not the actual number of bytes received over the network.

dfsrcSizeOfFilesReceived.name: dfsrcSizeOfFilesReceived
dfsrcSizeOfFilesReceived.description: Size of Files Received shows the uncompressed size (in bytes) of the files received on this connection. This is the number of bytes that would have been received had DFS Replication compression not been used.

dfsrcTotalBytesReceived.name: dfsrcTotalBytesReceived
dfsrcTotalBytesReceived.description: Total Bytes Received shows the total number of bytes received on the connection. The bytes received value includes file data and replication metadata.

dfsrcTotalFilesReceived.name: dfsrcTotalFilesReceived
dfsrcTotalFilesReceived.description: Total Files Received shows the number of files that were received on the connection.

dfsReplicationServiceVolumeTable.name: dfsReplicationServiceVolumeTable
dfsReplicationServiceVolumeTable.description: The DFS Replication service volume performance object. This object includes counters for update sequence number (USN) journal records and database processing on each volume.

dfsReplicationServiceVolumeEntry.name: dfsReplicationServiceVolumeEntry
dfsReplicationServiceVolumeEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'DFS Replication Service Volumes' object.

dfsrsvDatabaseCommits.name: dfsrsvDatabaseCommits
dfsrsvDatabaseCommits.description: Database Commits shows the number of database commit operations performed by the DFS Replication service. This counter indicates how intensive the DFS Replication service is from a database perspective.

dfsrsvDatabaseLookups.name: dfsrsvDatabaseLookups
dfsrsvDatabaseLookups.description: Database Lookups shows the number of database search operations performed by the DFS Replication service This counter indicates how intensive the DFS Replication service is from a database perspective.

dfsrsvUSNJournalRecordsAccepted.name: dfsrsvUSNJournalRecordsAccepted
dfsrsvUSNJournalRecordsAccepted.description: USN Journal Records Accepted shows the number of update sequence number (USN) journal records that were processed by the DFS Replication service. The DFS Replication service processes all USN journal records for replicated content on a volume and ignores records for non-replicated files and folders on the volume.

dfsrsvUSNJournalRecordsRead.name: dfsrsvUSNJournalRecordsRead
dfsrsvUSNJournalRecordsRead.description: USN Journal Records Read shows the number of update sequence number (USN) journal records that were read by the DFS Replication service.

dfsrsvUSNJournalUnreadPercentage.name: dfsrsvUSNJournalUnreadPercentage
dfsrsvUSNJournalUnreadPercentage.description: USN Journal Unread Percentage shows the percent of the update sequence number (USN) journal that has not yet been read and processed by the DFS Replication service. A journal wrap will occur if this counter reaches 100.

faxsFailedOutgoingConnections.name: faxsFailedOutgoingConnections
faxsFailedOutgoingConnections.description: Number of outgoing connections that failed.

faxsFailedReceptions.name: faxsFailedReceptions
faxsFailedReceptions.description: Number of faxes that service failed to receive.

faxsMinutesReceiving.name: faxsMinutesReceiving
faxsMinutesReceiving.description: Number of minutes that the service received faxes.

faxsMinutesSending.name: faxsMinutesSending
faxsMinutesSending.description: Number of minutes that the service spent in sending successfully transmitted faxes.

faxsTotalBytes.name: faxsTotalBytes
faxsTotalBytes.description: Total number of bytes sent and received.

faxsTotalFaxesSentAndReceived.name: faxsTotalFaxesSentAndReceived
faxsTotalFaxesSentAndReceived.description: Total number of faxes sent and received.

faxsTotalMinutesSendAndReceive.name: faxsTotalMinutesSendAndReceive
faxsTotalMinutesSendAndReceive.description: Total number of minutes that the service sent and received faxes.

faxsTotalPages.name: faxsTotalPages
faxsTotalPages.description: Total number of pages sent and received.

hcapcAverageNPSValidationTime.name: hcapcAverageNPSValidationTime
hcapcAverageNPSValidationTime.description: Average time taken by NPS to validate requests in milliseconds for this uptime

hcapcLastNPSValidationTime.name: hcapcLastNPSValidationTime
hcapcLastNPSValidationTime.description: Time taken by NPS to validate the last request in milliseconds for this uptime

ipsdIncorrectSPIPackets.name: ipsdIncorrectSPIPackets
ipsdIncorrectSPIPackets.description: Incorrect SPI packets is the number of packets for which the Security Parameter Index (SPI) was incorrect since the computer was last started. A large number of packets with bad SPIs within a short amount of time might indicate a packet spoofing attack.

ipsdOffloadedBytesReceivedPerSec.name: ipsdOffloadedBytesReceivedPerSec
ipsdOffloadedBytesReceivedPerSec.description: Offloaded Bytes Received per second is the rate of bytes received using IPsec hardware offload. Certain network adapters can accelerate IPsec processing by performing hardware offload of IPsec cryptographic functions.

ipsdOffloadedBytesSentPerSec.name: ipsdOffloadedBytesSentPerSec
ipsdOffloadedBytesSentPerSec.description: Offloaded Bytes Sent per second is the rate of bytes sent using IPsec hardware offload. Certain network adapters can accelerate IPsec processing by performing hardware offload of IPsec cryptographic functions.

ipsdOffloadedSecurityAssociation.name: ipsdOffloadedSecurityAssociation
ipsdOffloadedSecurityAssociation.description: Offloaded Security Associations is the number of active Quick Mode security associations offloaded to hardware. Certain network adapters can accelerate IPsec processing by performing hardware offload of IPsec cryptographic functions.

ipsdPacketsNotAuthenticated.name: ipsdPacketsNotAuthenticated
ipsdPacketsNotAuthenticated.description: Packets Not Authenticated is the number of packets for which data could not be verified (for which the integrity hash verification failed) since the computer was last started. Increases in this counter might indicate an IPsec packet spoofing or modification attack, or packet corruption by network devices.

ipsdPacketsNotDecrypted.name: ipsdPacketsNotDecrypted
ipsdPacketsNotDecrypted.description: Packets Not Decrypted is the number of packets that could not be decrypted since the computer was last started. A packet might not be decrypted if it fails a validation check.

ipsdPacketsReceivedOverWrongSA.name: ipsdPacketsReceivedOverWrongSA
ipsdPacketsReceivedOverWrongSA.description: Packets Received Over Wrong SA is the number of packets received over the wrong security association since the computer was last started.

ipsdPacketsFailedESPValidation.name: ipsdPacketsFailedESPValidation
ipsdPacketsFailedESPValidation.description: Packets That Failed ESP Validation is the number of packets received that failed ESP validation since the computer was last started.

ipsdPacketsFailedReplayDetection.name: ipsdPacketsFailedReplayDetection
ipsdPacketsFailedReplayDetection.description: Packets That Failed Replay Detection is the number of packets that contained an invalid sequence number since the computer was last started. Increases in this counter might indicate a network problem or replay attack.

ipsdPacketsFailUDPESPValidation.name: ipsdPacketsFailUDPESPValidation
ipsdPacketsFailUDPESPValidation.description: Packets That Failed UDP-ESP Validation is the number of packets received that failed UDP-ESP validation (used for NAT traversal) since the computer was last started.

msmqIncomingHTTPTraffic.name: msmqIncomingHTTPTraffic
msmqIncomingHTTPTraffic.description: The MSMQ Incoming HTTP Traffic and MSMQ Outgoing HTTP Session performance objects include counters that monitor messages sent over HTTP transport. These objects contain counters that monitor statistics about incoming HTTP messages, the rates at which the messages and message bytes arrive at the computer in an incoming HTTP connection, the total number of HTTP messages that arrived in the connection, and the total number of message bytes that arrived in the connection as well as counters that monitor the statistics about active outgoing HTTP sessions between the computer and other computers, the rates at which message bytes and messages are sent from the computer in a specific outgoing session, the total number of HTTP messages sent in the session, and the total number of message bytes sent in the session.

msmqitIncomingHTTPBytes.name: msmqitIncomingHTTPBytes
msmqitIncomingHTTPBytes.description: The total number of message bytes that arrived at the computer in the incoming HTTP connection.

msmqitIncomingHTTPBytesPerSec.name: msmqitIncomingHTTPBytesPerSec
msmqitIncomingHTTPBytesPerSec.description: The rate at which message bytes are arriving at the computer in the incoming HTTP connection.

msmqitIncomingHTTPMessages.name: msmqitIncomingHTTPMessages
msmqitIncomingHTTPMessages.description: The total number of HTTP Message Queuing messages that arrived at the computer.

msmqitIncomingHTTPMessagesPerSec.name: msmqitIncomingHTTPMessagesPerSec
msmqitIncomingHTTPMessagesPerSec.description: The rate at which HTTP Message Queuing messages are arriving at the computer.

msmqInMulticastSessionTable.name: msmqInMulticastSessionTable
msmqInMulticastSessionTable.description: The MSMQ Incoming Multicast Session and MSMQ Outgoing Multicast Session performance objects contain counters that monitor messages sent in multicast sessions. These objects contain counters that monitor statistics about active incoming multicast sessions, the rates at which the messages and message bytes arrive at the computer in a specific incoming multicast session, the total number of multicast messages that arrived in the session, and the total number of message bytes that arrived in the session as well as counters that monitor the statistics about active outgoing multicast sessions between the computer and other computers, the rates at which message bytes and messages are sent from the computer in a specific outgoing session, the total number of multicast messages sent in the session, and the total number of message bytes sent in the session.

msmqInMulticastSessionEntry.name: msmqInMulticastSessionEntry

msmqimsIncomingMulticastBytes.name: msmqimsIncomingMulticastBytes
msmqimsIncomingMulticastBytes.description: The total number of message bytes that arrived at the computer in the selected session.

msmqimsInMulticastBytesPerSec.name: msmqimsInMulticastBytesPerSec
msmqimsInMulticastBytesPerSec.description: The rate at which message bytes are arriving at the computer in the selected session.

msmqimsIncomingMulticastMessages.name: msmqimsIncomingMulticastMessages
msmqimsIncomingMulticastMessages.description: The total number of Message Queuing messages that arrived at the computer in the selected session.

msmqimsInMulticastMessagesPerSec.name: msmqimsInMulticastMessagesPerSec

msmqOutgoingHTTPSessionTable.description: The MSMQ Incoming HTTP Traffic and MSMQ Outgoing HTTP Session performance objects include counters that monitor messages sent over HTTP transport. These objects contain counters that monitor statistics about incoming HTTP messages, the rates at which the messages and message bytes arrive at the computer in an incoming HTTP connection, the total number of HTTP messages that arrived in the connection, and the total number of message bytes that arrived in the connection as well as counters that monitor the statistics about active outgoing HTTP sessions between the computer and other computers, the rates at which message bytes and messages are sent from the computer in a specific outgoing session, the total number of HTTP messages sent in the session, and the total number of message bytes sent in the session.

msmqOutMulticastSessionTable.name: msmqOutMulticastSessionTable
msmqOutMulticastSessionTable.description: The MSMQ Incoming Multicast Session and MSMQ Outgoing Multicast Session performance objects contain counters that monitor messages sent in multicast sessions. These objects contain counters that monitor statistics about active incoming multicast sessions, the rates at which the messages and message bytes arrive at the computer in a specific incoming multicast session, the total number of multicast messages that arrived in the session, and the total number of message bytes that arrived in the session as well as counters that monitor the statistics about active outgoing multicast sessions between the computer and other computers, the rates at which message bytes and messages are sent from the computer in a specific outgoing session, the total number of multicast messages sent in the session, and the total number of message bytes sent in the session.

msmqSessionTable.name: msmqSessionTable
msmqSessionTable.description: The MSMQ Session performance object is visible only when the computer has established an active session with another Message Queuing computer. This object contains counters that can be used to monitor statistics about active sessions between computers running Message Queuing. Multiple instances of this object may be listed, one for each session. There can be an instance of this object on both computers involved in each session up to the maximum number of instances allowed on each computer. Instance lists the IP address of the computer with which there is an active session.

searchGatherer.name: searchGatherer
searchGatherer.description: Counters for the Windows Search Service Gathering service object

sgActiveQueueLength.name: sgActiveQueueLength
sgActiveQueueLength.description: The number of documents waiting for robot threads. If this number is not 0, all threads should be filtering.

sgAdminClients.name: sgAdminClients
sgAdminClients.description: The number of currently connected administrative clients.

sgAllNotificationsReceived.name: sgAllNotificationsReceived
sgAllNotificationsReceived.description: The total number of notifications received from all notification sources including file system.

sgDelayedDocuments.name: sgDelayedDocuments
sgDelayedDocuments.description: The number of documents delayed due to site hit frequency rules.

sgDocumentEntries.name: sgDocumentEntries
sgDocumentEntries.description: The number of document entries currently in memory. Zero means no indexing activity is going on.

sgDocumentsDelayedRetry.name: sgDocumentsDelayedRetry
sgDocumentsDelayedRetry.description: The number of documents that will be retried after time-out. When this is non-zero, it means that the local server it is crawling is shut down.

sgDocumentsFiltered.name: sgDocumentsFiltered
sgDocumentsFiltered.description: The number of times a filter object was created. This corresponds to the total number of documents filtered in the system since startup.

sgDocumentsFilteredRate.name: sgDocumentsFilteredRate
sgDocumentsFilteredRate.description: The number of documents filtered per second.

sgDocumentsSuccessfullyFiltered.name: sgDocumentsSuccessfullyFiltered
sgDocumentsSuccessfullyFiltered.description: The number of documents successfully filtered.

sgDocumentsSuccessFilteredRate.name: sgDocumentsSuccessFilteredRate
sgDocumentsSuccessFilteredRate.description: The number of successfully filtered documents per second.

sgExtNotificationsRate.name: sgExtNotificationsRate
sgExtNotificationsRate.description: The rate of external notifications received per second.

sgExtNotificationsReceived.name: sgExtNotificationsReceived
sgExtNotificationsReceived.description: The total number of notifications received from all notification sources excluding file system.

sgFilterObjects.name: sgFilterObjects
sgFilterObjects.description: The number of filter objects in the system. Each filter object corresponds to a URL currently being filtered.

sgFilterProcessCreated.name: sgFilterProcessCreated
sgFilterProcessCreated.description: The total number of times a filter process was created or restarted. Having too many filter processes created indicates that filtering is having trouble with the data in the documents.

sgFilterProcesses.name: sgFilterProcesses
sgFilterProcesses.description: The number of filtering processes in the system.

sgFilterProcessesMax.name: sgFilterProcessesMax
sgFilterProcessesMax.description: The maximum number of filtering processes that have existed in the system since startup.

sgFilteringThreads.name: sgFilteringThreads
sgFilteringThreads.description: The total number of filtering threads in the system. This number is calculated based on your system resources.

sgHeartbeats.name: sgHeartbeats
sgHeartbeats.description: The total number of heartbeats counted since startup. A heartbeat occurs once every 10 seconds while the service is running. If the service is not running there will be no heartbeat and the number of ticks will not be incremented.

sgIdleThreads.name: sgIdleThreads
sgIdleThreads.description: The number of threads waiting for documents.

sgNotificationsRate.name: sgNotificationsRate
sgNotificationsRate.description: The rate of external notifications received per second.

sgPerformanceLevel.name: sgPerformanceLevel
sgPerformanceLevel.description: Indicates the level of the amount of system resources that the Gatherer service is allowed to use.

sgReasonToBackOff.name: sgReasonToBackOff
sgReasonToBackOff.description: The code describing why the Gatherer service went into back off state. 0 - up and running 1 - high system IO traffic 2 - high notifications rate 3 - delayed recovery in progress (not implemented) 4 - back off due to user activity 5 - Battery Low 6 - Memory Low 99 - back off for some internal reason (forced by Search itself) While backing off, no indexing is performed. To resume the indexing you must eliminate the reason for back off. If the Gatherer service is in back off state, the Search service is paused and there is a message in the event log.

sgServerObjects.name: sgServerObjects
sgServerObjects.description: The number of servers recently accessed by the system.

sgServerObjectsCreated.name: sgServerObjectsCreated
sgServerObjectsCreated.description: The number of times a new server object had to be created.

sgServersCurrentlyUnavailable.name: sgServersCurrentlyUnavailable
sgServersCurrentlyUnavailable.description: A server becomes unavailable when a number of requests to that server time out.

sgServersUnavailable.name: sgServersUnavailable
sgServersUnavailable.description: A server becomes unavailable when a number of requests to that server time out.

sgStemmersCached.name: sgStemmersCached
sgStemmersCached.description: Number of available cached stemmer instances. Too many may indicate a resource usage problem.

sgSystemIOTrafficRate.name: sgSystemIOTrafficRate
sgSystemIOTrafficRate.description: System IO (disk) traffic rate in KB/s detected by back off logic

sgThreadsAccessingNetwork.name: sgThreadsAccessingNetwork
sgThreadsAccessingNetwork.description: The number of threads waiting for a response from the filter process. If no activity is going on and this number is equal to number of filtering threads, it may indicate a network problem or unavailability of the server it is crawling.

sgThreadsInPlugIns.name: sgThreadsInPlugIns
sgThreadsInPlugIns.description: The number of threads waiting for plug-ins to complete an operation.

sgThreadsBlockedDueToBackOff.name: sgThreadsBlockedDueToBackOff
sgThreadsBlockedDueToBackOff.description: The number of threads blocked due to back off event

sgTimeOuts.name: sgTimeOuts
sgTimeOuts.description: The total number of timeouts detected by the system since startup.

sgWordBreakersCached.name: sgWordBreakersCached
sgWordBreakersCached.description: Number of available cached word breakers instances

wasActiveListenerChannels.name: wasActiveListenerChannels
wasActiveListenerChannels.description: Number of currently active listener channels in the worker process.

wasActiveProtocolHandlers.description: Number of currently active protocol handlers in the worker process.

wasHealthPingReplyLatency.name: wasHealthPingReplyLatency

wasTotalHealthPings.description: Total number of health pings received by the process.

wasTotalRequestsServed.name: wasTotalRequestsServed
wasTotalRequestsServed.description: Total number of requests served by the worker process. This counter is only meaningful when request based recycling is enabled for the application pool.

wasTotalRuntimeStatusQueries.name: wasTotalRuntimeStatusQueries
wasTotalRuntimeStatusQueries.description: Total number of Runtime Status queries received by the process.

wsrmPolicyTable.name: wsrmPolicyTable
wsrmPolicyTable.description: The WSRM Policy performance object, installed with Windows System Resource Manager (WSRM), consists of a counter that provides the percentage of CPU cycles of the entire system that are used by the current resource-allocation policy, since the time the policy was set to manage the behavior of WSRM. (The resource-allocation policy is an ordered list of resource allocations that specifies the management behavior of WSRM at a given time.) Each WSRM Policy object will have one instance whose name is the same as the current active policy.

wsrmPolicyEntry.name: wsrmPolicyEntry
wsrmPolicyEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'WSRM: Policy' object.

wsrmplSystemManagedCPUPercent.name: wsrmplSystemManagedCPUPercent
wsrmplSystemManagedCPUPercent.description: The percentage of CPU cycles managed by WSRM that are used by the combined process-matching criteria. A process-matching criterion is the mechanism in WSRM that matches running processes to a resource-allocation policy.

wsrmProcessTable.name: wsrmProcessTable
wsrmProcessTable.description: The WSRM Process performance object, installed with Windows System Resource Manager (WSRM), consists of a counter that provides the percentage of total managed CPU cycles used by a particular process, since the time that the resource-allocation policy was set to manage the behavior of WSRM. (The resource-allocation policy is an ordered list of resource allocations that specifies the management behavior of WSRM at a given time.) One instance of this object exists for every managed process. Note that Total Managed CPU cycles is the sum of the CPU cycles for all the managed processes.

wsrmProcessEntry.name: wsrmProcessEntry
wsrmProcessEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'WSRM: Process' object.

wsrmprActualManagedCPUPercent.name: wsrmprActualManagedCPUPercent
wsrmprActualManagedCPUPercent.description: The percentage of total managed CPU cycles that have been used by this process-matching criterion. A process-matching criterion is the mechanism in WSRM that matches running processes to a resource-allocation policy.

wsrmProcessMatchingCriteriaTable.name: wsrmProcessMatchingCriteriaTable
wsrmProcessMatchingCriteriaTable.description: The WSRM process-matching criteria performance object, installed with Windows System Resource Manager (WSRM), consists of counters that monitor the CPU usage and memory usage of the processes matched by the process-matching criteria. The criteria are included in the managing resource-allocation policy. Each object will have as many instances as the number of process-matching criteria within the current active policy.

wsrmProcessMatchingCriteriaEntry.name: wsrmProcessMatchingCriteriaEntry
wsrmProcessMatchingCriteriaEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'WSRM: Process Matching Criteria' object.

wsrmpmcActualManagedCPUPercent.name: wsrmpmcActualManagedCPUPercent
wsrmpmcActualManagedCPUPercent.description: The percentage of total managed CPU cycles that have been used by this process-matching criterion. A process-matching criterion is the mechanism in WSRM that matches running processes to a resource-allocation policy.

wsrmpmcManagedCPUPercent.name: wsrmpmcManagedCPUPercent
wsrmpmcManagedCPUPercent.description: The percentage of managed CPU cycles used by this process-matching criterion between the last process samplings.

wsrmpmcPageFileMBytes.name: wsrmpmcPageFileMBytes
wsrmpmcPageFileMBytes.description: The total size of page files used by this process.

wsrmpmcProcessCount.name: wsrmpmcProcessCount
wsrmpmcProcessCount.description: The number of processes associated with this process-matching criterion.

wsrmpmcTargetManagedCPUPercent.name: wsrmpmcTargetManagedCPUPercent
wsrmpmcTargetManagedCPUPercent.description: The percentage of total managed CPU cycles allocated to this process-matching criterion.

wsrmpmcWorkingSetMBytes.name: wsrmpmcWorkingSetMBytes
wsrmpmcWorkingSetMBytes.description: The total size of the set of memory pages used by the threads of this process.
